text:
#somethingforeveryone made by community for community, on www.rainieravenueradio.world. listen online or on the tunein app.

friday nov 23rd

10:30am @seamonsterradio 
ep 10 - celebrating women of the sea monster lounge. every song played this week will feature women with a connection to the sea monster lounge. we also interview karen "kz" zamm, kate olson and michelle searle, discussing how they help the community, the topic of the #metoo movement and how it's affecting seattle, and more. artists played include champagne honeybee, clarkia cobb, liberty strikes, marina christopher, syrinx effect and more surprises.

11:30am #singlefather project by @jalalwilson1
ep 38 - teaching children to overcome obstacles and overcoming obstacles as parents.

noon #fitness corner with mark bryant @worldchamp2000
ep 24 - big-t taurus niumata talked about his first powerlifting world championship.

12:30pm #seniors matter with brenda charles-edwards ep 63 - live 11/23/18 12:30pm.

1pm seattle here & now by john yasutake 
ep 62 - officer jim ritter, the lgbtq liaison of the seattle police department talks about his role with the department in serving this population.

2pm #communityspotlight 
ep 44 - the @seattlepubliclibrary chief librarian, marcellus turner interviewed by yvette dinish.

2:30pm you can make a difference with mac macgregor @thegendersensei
ep 32 - jalair box, one of the founders of speak out seattle, prioritizes public safety, focuses on what works to solve homelessness, and supports substance abuse prevention and treatment.

3pm the other side with rev robert jeffrey 
ep 28 - rabbi david basior of kadima reconstructionist community reflects on the pittsburgh synogogue shooting and the killings of 2 african americans in kentucky.

3:30pm mondo's world 
ep 43 - program manager for outdoors for all foundation, alex jones, shares how his organization assists disabled veterans and people in wheelchairs to mountain bike, cycle, ski, kayak, and more.

4pm #trafficjam

text:
urge incontinence is the involuntary loss of urine accompanied by strong urge.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
urge creates a sense of “fight or flight” throughout your body, and part of that reaction is the detrusor muscle in your bladder contracts to release urine.  no matter how strong your pelvic floor is, if those signals are firing, you’re going to leak.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
try this tip ⬆️ next time.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
✊pelicula feminista✊ 
seeing allred (2018)

gloria allred es una abogada que lleva toda su vida luchando por los derechos de las mujeres víctimas de abusos sexuales. ha sido insultada y caricaturizada por los medios de comunicación, pero, sin ella, casos como tan mediáticos como los de bill cosby, donald trump o harvey weinstein no habrían saltado a la luz pública. este documental de roberta grossman y sophie sartain es lo que todos necesitamos ver en la era del movimiento #metoo, donde las voces de las mujeres por fin son escuchadas. por suerte, allred siempre las escuchó

text:
för den som pallar så har jag startat en kanal som heter samlagen & staden på soundcloud. jag använder den lite som ett sätt för mig att försöka prata fritt och högt om allt som hänt i mitt liv. i mina 2 senaste väldigt oklippta avsnitt så pratar jag om min rättsprocess med fokus på vad som hände den där dagen då polisen ringde och hur jag idag försöker kämpa med mina skuldkänslor som dyker upp i sexuella sammanhang. det är jobbig lyssning och jag tänker att jag delar med mig av min historia för att andra ska känna att de inte är ensamma. vi behöver inte bära skulden på egen hand!
#metoo #oneyearaftermetoo #övergrepp #podcast #överleva #sexuellhälsa #psykiskohälsa

text:
i have learned that gratitude is all about perspective. a willingness to see all of the experiences in our lives as valuable. 
many young girls and women have shown me the meaning of true gratitude. the ability to be thankful and to find joy even in the midst of great struggle or pain.

they have inspired me to be grateful for all parts of my existence. they have helped me to desire less, and to see that i am surrounded by endless blessings and miracles. ✨🙏🏼

text:
🏵 sofia
reż. meryem benm'barek-aloïsi
.
🌟 premiera w kinie zorza: 23 listopada
_
_
🏆 nominacja do złotej kamery na mff w cannes 2018
_
📄 za pozamałżeński seks w maroku niezamężnym kobietom grozi kara od miesiąca do roku więzienia. może dlatego 20-letnia sofia (maha alemi) wypiera ze świadomości zaawansowaną już ciążę? gdy jednak doznaje silnych bólów brzucha podczas rodzinnej kolacji, na którą zaproszona jest para zamożnych znajomych, ich studiująca medycynę córka léna (sarah perles) szybko diagnozuje stan koleżanki. widząc desperację sofii, pomaga jej urodzić w sekrecie, ale noworodka długo ukrywać się nie da. razem rozpoczynają poszukiwania ojca dziecka oraz sposobu, by nie okryć hańbą rodziny. pełnometrażowy debiut wychowanej w belgii marokańskiej reżyserki meryem benm'barek, będąc krytyką patriarchalnego społeczeństwa, jednocześnie portretuje kobiety w złożony, daleki od prostej wiktymizacji, sposób.
_
_
_
_
_

text:
you've all posted engagement/wedding/pregnancy announcements/updates and/or baby pics, well, life works in different ways for others! .
i have been travelling for a few years and am currently in peru continuing my education but my anxiety and ptsd issues that decided to return a few years ago? yeah, they came back with a vengance. i've done the work- drugs, medications - hated both but worked as temporary band-aid solutions- , hours of therapy as well to develop a toolbox of tricks for when issues arise- but there was nothing left this time. i needed help, got help, and the resulting consensus was for an emotional therapy support animal. .
so,  my 5 year old fur-baby named pelusa (long hair/fluffy in spanish) decided to adopt me and yes, there will be many more photos of her to come!! 48 hours into our forever relationship, we're adjusting well 😁❤️ we've made it to school and discovered the joys of the park nearby and yes, she totally snuggles up at night for bedtime bellyrubs. she doesn't know what to do with her pink bear because i don't think she's ever had a toy before but she was so tired she passed right out! and she's started using her bowls (instead of insisting on eating out of my hand) .
.
.
.

text:
dear best friend, "meeting you was fate but being with you was my best choice"

neither did you expressed your love nor you have said that. but in your fights, taunts and scolds you made me realize that more adorable than it would have been expressed. because self-realization is beautiful in its own way. 
from laughing at my lame jokes to controlling laughter at my super jokes from a stranger you became my amigo. making my sad tears fall down the cheeks as happy tears you cared me like a sibling in their absence. 
giving an ear to my blunders and never-ending  talks to a hand on my shoulder with words "it's ok!" you easily handled my weird moods. you simply amazed me by switching to different roles within a span of seconds.  astonishing me with words of motivation during the period of difficulties to being a constant supporter in front of the world you have never left a stone to awe me. no matter what i did, you never judged me instead corrected me.  no matter how bad and stupid i'm, you loved me unconditionally. while people laughed at the stains of blood behind my dress you respected the womanhood in me. 
while you been stern and rigid, at an instance, i felt too, kick you up. yet! only to realize later you were pulling me from stepping on pricks of hardships and hurdles. you loved me as a sister and respected me as a girl.

while i was enjoying the most beautiful journey of life you entered and made the life more dramatic. while others paved a way out of my life in worst days you shined and glowed like a diya of clout and courage. you came to my life and scorched the demons in me and of my life. moreover, you gave me another family, you been my prodigy and the best treasure of life.
.
.
swetha prabhu.
(@swethagprabhu)
.
.

text:
once upon a time you had it all sorted out, and then you didn't. as we talk to our church family, many are in the wandering. looking for a new church home. i know the anguish, anxiety,  and heartache this poses for many. we were there too. but i pray you follow the holy spirit and seek your next steps.
god will guide you and bring you new friends, dreams, passions,  and desires. you will make a difference, and will be appreciated for your giftings.
the word will come alive....again, and you will find the fire in your soul to help others. it will take some time to heal. but you will be able to help others while you heal. wounded healers. 
in anything you recover from, it's more about what you say yes to. "may you be an explorer, may you recover delight and wonder and curiosity and your faith about god, and about the story with which you continue to wrestle." sarah bessey-out of sorts
we love you. and we love our new church home, family life community church.  #churchfamily #littlefamily #familylife #hopegiver #mommyhood  #makeadifference #outofsorts #propelwomen #lifeischoice #voicetothevoiceless

text:
a group of women and girls, all of whom are related, in the city of villa fiorito. 
despite a 2012 law which raised the maximum prison sentence for “femicide,” the killing of a woman or girl on account of her gender, argentina is still struggling against widespread gender-based violence. thankfully, a grassroots, women-led movement known as ni una menos (not one [woman] less) has arisen in argentina, and is working to empower women and defend their human rights. in this series, karl mancini (@karlitomancini) shares some of his work on the inspiring women of ni una menos and their fight for justice. to learn more about both mancini's work and ni una menos, please follow the link in our bio. 
#opensociety #argentina #niunamenos #femicide #femicidio #conmisderechosnotemetas #16days #genderbasedviolence #metoo #hearmetoo

text:
“i believe you” is one of the most powerful phrases a #survivor can hear. it opens the avenue to healing, to self-acceptance, and to communication. too many times survivors are told that what happened to them is somehow “false” (🙄) or they are made out to be “the bad guys”. which is completely ridiculous and harmful. it makes others much more hesitant to speak up and out, when now, more than ever, we need voices. to have someone, in one of the highest positions, sit and listen to you and say, “i see you. i hear you. i believe you.” - is truly empowering. .
.
.
when i went to work with rose, i was nervous, having never photographed a judge before; but this was an experience of a lifetime. she really is one of the kindest people and this shoot is easily in my top 5 favorites that i’ve ever done. while she heard so many people, with the case that went viral, she is also out healing people on a personal level. myself included. i’m honored to call her a friend. ♥️
.
.
.
.
“you never need to be someone else. you matter. i see you. i hear you. i believe you.” - honorable @authoraquilina .
.
.
.

text:
#justbecause

#justbecause i happen to look at you doesn't mean i am interested in you.

#justbecause i smile and talk doesn't mean i am easy to approach.

#justbecause i don't raise my voice to create a hue and cry doesn't mean 'something' went unnoticed.

#justbecause i wear  traditional doesn't mean i have to be addressed with 'respect' publically and attempted personally.

#justbecause

this post is not another #metoo movement or any gender-specific voice. it is about day-to-day living, dealing people and daily interactions. 
it's weird how people draw conclusions without even knowing you and it's worse when they create an uncomfortable environment for you #justbecause you choose to take a stand not by making noise but by changing responses. 
if only it was easier to live and let live safely!

if safety was just about being physically safe, we would all hire body guards as we hire helpers for our daily odds.

safety has a lot to do with the mind and heart.  and sadly, we can only guard our own mind and heart to feel mentally and emotionally safe.

#justbecause  it's your mind, so only you can fix it.

#justbecause

text:
clothing and underwear is submitted for dna evidence after a sexual assault or rape. that evidence is often then turned around and manipulated in court to suggest that that person was ‘asking for it’ due to the type of clothing that they were wearing. 
no means no. no does not mean yes under any circumstances. it does not mean yes if you’re wearing ‘provocative’ clothing or underwear, nor does it mean yes if that person manipulates you to be sexually intimate, or if you’ve previously had consensual sex, or spoke about having sexual encounters prior, or consented and then withdrew that consent. if someone says no you respect their wishes, you do not carry on, you do not persist in manipulating them or use physical or emotional force to get what you want. you stop. 
know that when you say no, in whatever way that is, you should be respected. however, the absence of no does not mean yes. there are many situations when someone might not be able to say no; for example they may be asleep, unconscious, intoxicated, scared, in shock, etc. yes cannot be implied, assumed, or emotionally manipulated. if that is not respected then that is an offense. 
education about what consent is is needed. the fact consent is having to be explained so frequently proves that. @thegeminiproj is a non profitable organisation campaigning for mandatory consent education in all uk schools. 
please go and support their page and let’s put an end to sexual assault and harassment together!

text:
📌trastornos del carácter 📌degeneración del cutis
📌obesidad
📌problemas ginecologicos
las consecuencias negativas cuando el qi no fluye.

en la sociedad moderna las mujeres soportamos una doble presión, el trabajo y la familia en su cotidianidad. la crianza y las responsabilidades laborales y de sustento parecen ser tópicos casi imposibles de conciliar aunque la sociedad patriarcal nos lo haya hecho creer. además de esto, vivimos en un mundo, donde nos creemos lineales y nosotras somos cíclicas. toda esta desconexión con nuestra esencia nos lleva al desequilibrio, a la inestabilidad, la depresión, a la impaciencia y a la tristeza. todos esos altibajos en nuestro estado anímico provocan lo que en medicina china llamamos estancamiento del qi.
cuando ese libre curso de la energía a través de los meridianos es bloqueado, se produce estancamiento, afecta a la sangre y a los órganos internos provocando todo tipo de desequilibrio. 
la obstrucción de los meridianos y y la desarmonía entre el qi y la sangre, el yang y el yin constituyen un gran daño a la salud femenina.
esto no solamente afectan la apariencia y anticipan la vejez, sino que también perjudican seriamente la salud.

según estadísticas, las mujeres de 25 años para arriba padecen problemas de piel y acné y envejecimiento precoz,  un 31% tienen enfermedades ginecológicas de mioma uterino, masas en los senos y quistes de ovario. entre las mujeres de 30 años para arriba, la tasa de incidencia de masas en los senos llega a un 49%, y las masas en los senos son susceptibles de evolucionar a cáncer de mama.
estás tristes estadísticas nos hablan de que todavía tenemos mucho por hacer para con nosotras mismas.
la medicina china proporciona desde la acupuntura y la farmacopea, herramientas para lograr ese equilibrio de manera natural y haciéndonos tomar responsabilidad sobre nuestra salud. nuestro cuerpo, nosotras decidimos.
#medicinatradicionalchina #acupuntura#ginecologianatural #sanapordentrobellaporfuera #enpoweringwomen #metoo #menew#frommetootomenew

text:
my reason 💕

i want these two incredible humans to know that anything is possible. to know that they can achieve anything they set their minds to and then some!! to know they are entitled to equality, to be heard, to have a voice, to be treated with respect, to say no, to be strong and powerful. they are why i do what i do. they are part of my reason part of my why, why i learn; i develop myself; i got through severe anxiety; i left the corporate world; i became a coach; i have faced my past; i chose a different path with someone new. why i continue forward. why i said no. ✨
✨
my journey to here was challenging. i am a survivor. i am a #metoo  i am someone who has tentatively put one foot in front of the other. i said no to the bullies, the controllers, the abusers. i have been brave and found my courage. ⛅️
every cloud!!
☀️
☀️
the sun shone brightly the days they were both born. it shone in my heart and my soul. to have daughters is a true blessing. (i am biased i know!) i am not a perfect mummy, because there is no such thing. i am me. and i want to show them that life’s traumas don’t have to be a barrier to having an amazing life just the way you want. 🌈
i didn’t end up in the gutter on drink and drugs and equally i didn’t become a ball breaking man hating extreme high flyer. i could have gone either way. i simply survived with one foot, then another and every time i fell, i got up, i brushed myself down and i put one foot in front of the other from a very young age. ✨
✨
i didn’t always have these two incredible humans as part of my reason and my why. i’ve always found strength to keep going. but here’s the thing, now they are part of my reason and my why it makes me even more determined to carry on being brave and most of all to help other women be brave, be courageous, take back control and be magnificent 💫🌈 we all have a reason, a why somewhere.  take a moment, dig deep and find your reason, find your why. 💕😊 #reason #yourreason #why #yourwhy #findyourwhy #survivor #metoo #bullies #control #abuse #future #transforming #transformation #mindset #mentalhealth #anxiety #mentalwellness #mentalwellbeing #trauma #equality #lifecoachforwomen

text: we can get caught up in assumptions we make and then the thoughts around them when we feel threatened. these thoughts aren’t real so if you feel that you’re going down the rabbit hole, stop, take some deep breaths and ask yourself what is fact and what is your fear. these two are very different. like my nanny used to say “don’t worry until you have a reason to worry.” work off the facts and don’t make assumptions.

text:
a group of women and girls, all of whom are related, in the city of villa fiorito. 
despite a 2012 law which raised the maximum prison sentence for “femicide,” the killing of a woman or girl on account of her gender, argentina is still struggling against widespread gender-based violence. thankfully, a grassroots, women-led movement known as ni una menos (not one [woman] less) has arisen in argentina, and is working to empower women and defend their human rights. in this series, karl mancini (@karlitomancini) shares some of his work on the inspiring women of ni una menos and their fight for justice. to learn more about both mancini's work and ni una menos, please follow the link in our bio. 
#opensociety #argentina #niunamenos #femicide #femicidio #conmisderechosnotemetas #16days #genderbasedviolence #metoo #hearmetoo

-kshitij

text:
“time’s up” - acrylic on canvas 
new work for the #45series 
addressing the women’s right to be heard in all manners of life. i was inspired by an article from @thecut during the #kavanaughhearings. 
for centuries she has only been able to listen (hence the ear peeking out), not speak. mixing the medieval “scold bridle” device, that was used as a punishment for being too chiding and annoying, with a 21st century woman wearing @alexandermcqueen  shows that even today women are struggling to be heard. additionally the objectification of women is juxtaposed with the strength and fight to speak up -including women owning their sexuality.
this painting is quite personal to me in many ways, so i dressed her in one of my favorite designers and added one or two of my features.
#timesup #metoo #believesurvivors 
#speakup #scoldbridle #alexandermcqueen #painting #art #acrylic #canvas

text:
demain est un jour symbolique et qui a une grande importance pour moi. parce que c'est moi, peut-être vous, une amie, une tante, une voisine. parce que c'est #noustoutes. parce que c'est trop fréquent, je le constate bien trop souvent autour de moi. 😓
.

qu'elle soit psychologique, verbale ou physique, la violence reste de la violence, il n'y a pas de "moins pire" et que souvent une forme en entraîne une autre... et tue autant de l'intérieur que de l'extérieur. .

demain samedi 24 c'est la marche pour la lutte contre les #violences faites aux #femmes. le #violet est la couleur de ralliement et de soutien. n'hésitez pas à soutenir la cause avec @noustoutes2411
en postant une photo en violet avec le #noustoutes, car en parler, libérer la parole sur ce #tabou et fléau, peu aider à libérer la parole d' une femme victime de violences autour de vous. 💜🙅‍♀️ libérer la #parole c'est briser l'emprise.
.
ou bien d'aller marcher toutes ensembles (et les hommes aussi !) le 24, départ 14h d'opéra. j'y serais 💜.
. 
#luttecontrelesviolencesfaitesauxfemmes #stopviolence #feministe
#feminist #metoo #jemarchele24  #parlonsen

text:
there is no sexual harassment without sexual corruption (mental corruption). what has a 3months old or 70years old grandmother done to warrant rape?

the violence against persons’ prohibition act (vappa) accords the national agency for the prohibition of trafficking in persons (naptip) the responsibility of operationalising and implementing the vapp act 2015. the vapp act couldn't see the light of the day until after 14years of hardwork to have the bill passed. as a law passed by the national assembly, the juridical scope of operation of the vappa is limited to the fct. state houses of assembly will need to pass the law to suit their governance context before it is operational at the state level. 
the challenge however is that the scope of the problem of sexual violence and violation transcends the fct. it is an issue of utmost public interest and concern across nigeria and globally as evidenced by the presence of sexual referral centres in states such as kaduna, lagos and ekiti and the #metoo movement. it can equally be inferred in the national outrage that followed the recent tragic case of the 13 year old ochanya ogbanje who died following years of sexual abuse within the family. 
there is a need to create a national register which exposes perpetrators of any form of abuse to reduce the increasing rates of violence in our society. we need to name and shame them.

at this point, everyone should be part of this amazing work. support the cause!  #endgbv #womennotobjects #warif

text:
oh the tears i have shed.
i don’t think i knew what weeping was until i looked at my daughter and thought about how i’ve treated myself all these years. from addictive and compulsive behaviors started by my body dysmorphia to sexual abuse to obsessive weight control issues to the depths of a nearly successful suicide attempt... i weep because during my whole life i have loved almost everyone and everything but myself. i’ve abused and been abused and my life experience as a whole has been a really tough pill to swallow. i spend a lot of... well i used to spend a lot of time hating myself. stuck on these repeat records of hate speech.
“you’re a loser” “you’re fat” “you’re damaged” “no ones going to want you” “you’re never going to accomplish anything” “you should die” “everyone else would be better off if you were gone”
what would i do if i heard my daughter say that to herself? will i be able to tell her she’s beautiful like my mom tried to tell me? will i be able to brush the hair out of her face and make her believe in herself when the first boy she loves breaks her heart or god forbid sexually abuse her like i have been?
i will be able to help my daughter ... if i can start doing that to myself and stay true to the course. all this time i just needed to start forgiving that girl that made those decisions for the better part of twenty years.... twenty years. now i get to be the women i never would have listened to. that’s how i’ll help ari. that’s how i’ll help myself. i’m only so candid because i know that there just has to be other people out there like me. i also know that i will be judged for being honest and i’m cool with that too - it’s just a weeding out process. don’t fear the process. don’t suffer. find your tribe. you don’t have to shout it from the rooftops but don’t withdraw into yourself... a sick mind is too dangerous a neighborhood to walk alone in.. reach out ♥️ and have a beautiful weekend people.
#ariagrayson #newmomlife #stayinspired #raisestrongwomen #itsoktonotbeok #bodypositive #recovery #depressionrecovery #bpdawareness #metoo #bereal #bestrong  #anoxeriarecovery #bulimarecovery #loveyourself

text:
swipe. ⬅️
.
in northern ireland we have currently have funding to give people seeking an abortion the opportunity to travel to the uk. this is not good enough, our people need access to basic healthcare on our soil. people i know personally have found themselves trapped with violent partners that use rape as a weapon to impregnate them and hold them further hostage. in abusive domestic relationships people do not have the luxury to step out their front doors without their abuser lurking never mind on to a plane to another country. moreover many people seeking an abortion are already parents, so having an abortion over seas would mean arranging babysitting, and explaining your situation to work in an environment potentially  hostile to your circumstances. online abortion pill raids are on the rise in northern ireland and our bodily autonomy is being used as political football. our current abortion laws (so ancient they’re older than the creation of the lightbulb) restrict us from seeking healthcare within our 6 counties, without the threat of being reported under suspicion of a forced miscarriage and potentially dragged from our homes to be humiliated in front of our communities by our own police. the law states a life sentence to any person that has an abortion in northern ireland, yet on average 28 people a week have an abortion from northern ireland by traveling to the uk. and over 28 people a week have an abortion if you include those staying home locked in a bathroom clutching online pills (and hopefully not a bottle of bleach.) these laws do not stop abortions, only increase the chances they are unsafe. pro life that’s a lie, you don’t care if women die. 
i tied the recent rape trial in with this because it’s all connected.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
there is a stress gap between men and women
________
studies show that women are twice as likely to suffer from anxiety and sever stress (surprise!) - we experience more insomnia, and even when we do get a full night of sleep, it is usually filled with problem-solving dreams. so we wake up as tired as we were the night before. 
________
in many cases (but not all), women do more (sometimes x3) of unpaid domestic work, than men. i highly encourage our well-working system : i cooked, you clean lol 
also - stop assuming that domestic chores are not work. every little bit is!
________
female managers (and others) are more likely to display “surface acting,” - or forcing emotions that are not felt (tell me about it...) surface acting is a form of emotional labor. yup. 
it’s not easy to pretend like you’re not surrounded by idiots. 
my advice:
we all should just go on the emotional labor strike.

text:
i google your name at 11:02 p.m. cause all i want now is to see a recent photograph of you. one you took within the last week.

yesterday i wanted to know if you are okay. i refreshed your blog but there was nothing new. no new sad poem.

day before yesterday i stared at your phone number for half an hour at 09:02 a.m. but i couldn't think of anything to say to you.

a day before that i couldn't stop myself from opening that folder in my laptop i have saved as your nickname. i read our old conversations. i listened to your voice notes and i cried over the same things once again.

a day before that i wrote a poem about you and i smiled when i read it cause it looked like you.

a day before that i thought all day about the things i would ask you if i ever talked to you and i counted 26 questions that wouldn't offend you. 
a day before that nothing mattered to me. not you. not me. not my feelings or your feelings. i was sure my heart had turned into stone.

it's 05:04 a.m. now and a new day. i am still thinking about you and i just want to know what was the last thing that made you laugh. /sahiba

.
if you have thoughts of ending your life or harming yourself, seek help from the nearest 24h emergency medical service;
or call your local befriending service.
☎️ samaritans of singapore 24h hotline: 1800-222-4444 ☎️
.
i was raped, more than once, by someone who was close to me, someone that i trusted.
.
i started writing my survivor story, pieced together from the entries in my journal, as well as my own suicide note.
.
i underestimated how hard writing this would be on me;
and how it would affect me emotionally and mentally.
.
it’s a long journey ahead of me.
but i have all the help that i need from family, friends, as well as a very good support group and help from the people in the sexual assault care centre.
.
☎️ sexual assault care centre hotline: +65 6779 0282 (monday-friday; 10 am - midnight)
.

text:
la giornata internazionale contro la violenza sulle donne, istituita dall’assemblea delle nazioni unite nel 1999, invita tutti noi a riflettere su un problema enorme, purtroppo ancora lontano da una soluzione. 
la violenza contro le donne si manifesta in vari modi: violenza fisica, violenza sessuale, lo stupro e la violenza psicologica. spesso a compiere queste violenze sono i partner o gli ex-partner che talvolta spingono le situazioni all’estremo con i casi di femminicidio. 
noi di fucina n.4 vogliamo cogliere l’invito alla riflessione sul tema analizzandolo da un punto di vista differente: quello degli uomini maltrattanti. per fare questo abbiamo invitato per il 26 novembre a motta di livenza l’associazione pordenonese in prima persona - uomini contro la violenza sulle donne. questa associazione, fondata nel novembre del 2016, riunisce una trentina di iscritti di diversa provenienza professionale ed età. tra i principali obiettivi ci sono la costituzione di un centro di ascolto per uomini maltrattanti e degli incontri di sensibilizzazione con le scuole. interverranno due soci fondatori del gruppo, antonio aprea e lo psichiatra carlo rizzo, che affronteranno il problema della violenza maschile e del "maltrattante della porta accanto". insieme a loro saranno presenti l’attrice bianca manzari con la quale approfondiremo alcune letture e pablo perissinotto cantautore che da qualche tempo collabora con l’associazione.

in prima persona: parole e musica contro la violenza sulle donne
lunedì 26 novembre, ore 20.45
sala della loggia, motta di livenza (tv)
interverranno:
* antonio aprea, socio fondatore di in prima persona * carlo rizzo, psichiatra * bianca manzari, attrice * pablo perissinotto, cantautore

#fucinan4 #mottadilivenza #inprimapersona #violenzadonne #violenzadigenere #25novembre #biancamanzari #pabloperissinotto #metoo #feminism #feminist #treviso #oderzo #veneto #pordenone

text:
♥️ 🔴 ♥️
la violencia contra la mujer es una de los problemas más álgidos en estos tiempos de la humanidad. eso ya lo sabemos. lo que queremos es ahora es dar un paso adelante y sanar.

sanar desde nosotras, con herramientas, interiormente, desde nuestra paz, desde el amor, con el poder de la autotransformación hasta sanar al ser humano sin distinción, la humanidad, el mundo, el universo.

he escuchado de un vestido que está en movimiento, en evolución, en ebullición!... he escuchado a mujeres decir "escucha a tu corazón, sigue tu intuición, sigue tu vestido"... el vestido dice "soy paz ♥️ soy amor ♥️ soy poder ♥️ soy mujer... me visto de paz, amor, mujer y poder... es el movimiento ♥️ global del vestido!... es #thedressmovement ♥️. y el movimiento se inicia contigo, conmigo, con nosotras que marcharemos el 24 de noviembre como parte de la marcha #nosotrasexigimos en la sección cultura, educación.  nos reuniremos al lado del obelisco en el campo de marte a las 3pm. iremos vestidas de #elvestidodecorazones ♥️, polos de corazones ♥️, pañuelos ♥️, bufandas ♥️, etc. o vestidas de blanco (falda o pantalón,short, etc). ¿qué haremos? <3 seremos  un grupo pacifico ♥️, amoroso ♥️ y poderoso ♥️
bailaremos en círculo ⭕️ ♥️ 🔴 y creando la cadena.
cantaremos "soy paz, soy amor, soy poder, confío en mí", el río está fluyendo, en espiral ⭕️ hacia el centro, es aquí donde quiero estar junto a ti... ♥️♥️
♥️ nos detendremos en silencio, en meditación, en contemplación.
♥️ cantaremos mantras.
♥️ disfrutaremos de diferentes danzas espontáneas.
♥️ bailaremos espontáneas, seremos y estaremos.

notas importantes: ♥️ ¡queremos que vengas con tus hijos! sentimos que es una oportunidad histórica y educativa que querrás compartir con ellos. entenderemos si tuvieras que dejar el desfile temprano para mejor servir sus necesidades.  a la discreción de cada mamá, desde su paz, su amor, y su gran poder. somos uno 🔴⭕️♥️.
♥️ pueden comprar polos, bufandas, pañuelos, vestidos de corazones a través de esta página o al whatsapp 990048889. ♥️ convoquemos a nuestros contactos para caminar juntas. todas y todos invitados!!!)
#nosotrasexigimos #thedressmovement #soypazsoyamorsoypodersoymujer

text:
at 10 years old we begin to lose our self-confidence!  how sad!! we then spend our 30s, 40s, and 50s trying to build it back up again!  if we can take the time now to take care of ourselves and un-do the messages we’ve received over the years, we will be able to be more content with ourselves and our lives.  for those who have daughters, by taking care of us we can be positive role models to them on self-love, self-compassion, and following our dreams 💖

if you’d like to learn how for either you or your daughter, schedule a complimentary call with me by clicking on the link in my bio ▶️ @denisestyer

text:
seven years ago, iran's bill for the protection of women against violence made it to parliament. seven years later, it's being reviewed by religious leaders while women and girls across the country--especially those with disabilities--remain vulnerable to various forms of violence with no legal protections. in a statement issued ahead of the international day for the elimination of violence against women, the center for human rights in iran calls upon the iranian authorities to engage civil society, listen to women's rights activist and prioritize and pass this legislation before more innocent women and girls are endangered due to the lack of legal protections in iran. read our in-depth report about this important issue on our website.⠀
⠀
#internationaldaytoeliminateviolenceagainstwomen #survivor #domesticabusesurvivor #vawg #orangetheworld #hearmetoo #iran #womensrights #humanrights #metoo

text: už ste to počuli? ☎️ @bratislavaiff sa tento rok v sekcii lexikón zameria na tému “ženský pohľad”. “posledný rok bol nielen v kinematografii rokom #metoo a aj preto sme sa rozhodli na mff bratislava reflektovať postavenie žien – v spoločnosti i v kinematografii. zvolili sme si tému ženský pohľad ako protipól k mužskému pohľadu ako ho identifikovala filmová teoretička laura mulvey. v sekcii dávame priestor ženským autorkám, snažíme sa upozorniť na ženskú skúsenosť, ktorá je vo filme i v spoločnosti neraz opomínaná, reflektujeme to, ako boli a sú ženy vo filmoch zobrazované, a pripomíname, že žánre nie sú mužské a ženské,“ hovoria zostavovatelia sekcie a naši redaktori v jednom, @ujoedo a @huncutikova. #savethedate #femalegaze #filmfestival #womeninfilmmaking #girlsinfilm #womenfilmmakers #bratislavaiff #dnespozeram #topicofthemonth #filmindustry #filmmaking #cinema #poddokina #kinecko

text_retweet:
#repost @gitanabavi (@get_repost)
・・・
kom ihåg black friday! 
ja, alltså inte den som vill att du ska köpa så mycket som möjligt, utan den från 1910, då 300 suffragetter samlades utanför westminsterpalatset i london för att demonstrera för kvinnlig rösträtt. dagen blev känd som "black friday" för att de manliga poliserna, och de manliga åskådarna, mötte de kvinnliga demonstranterna med våld. delar av våldet var sexualiserat – bland annat vred polisen om flera demonstranters bröst, och en del våldshandlingar åtföljdes av vidriga, kränkande kommentarer.

några få generationer senare är året 2018 och vi förknippar "black friday" med köphets.

2018 har vi här i sverige äntligen fått en sexualbrottslagstiftning som definierar våldtäkt för vad det verkligen är; ofrivilligt sex, och som gör det möjligt att döma för våldtäkt även när gärningspersonen (som oftast är en man) saknar uppsåt. så många generationer av feminister står bakom den lagen, och vi hade aldrig kommit hit om det inte vore för våra historiska medsystrar, bland annat suffragetterna. 
och vi fortsätter!

just nu uppmärksammar vi de delar av vår politik som har starkast koppling till #metoo, bland annat vill vi: ♀ att åklagarmyndigheten och domstolsverket ges ökade resurser i syfte att kvalitetshöja rättsprocessen inom sexualbrott.
♀ se en skarp lagstiftning mot könsdiskriminerande reklam, en begränsning av porr och ett förbud mot strippklubbar, för att våra offentliga rum ska vara trygga för alla.
♀ att sverige genomför informationssatsningar kring samtycke och vad den nya lagen innebär.

och vi ska: ♀ verka för sexuella och reproduktiva rättigeter i eu enligt svensk modell, för våra medsyskons rätt till abort och samtyckeslagstiftning.

skriv under uppropet om du stöttar våra politiska förslag:
https://med.feministisktinitiativ.se/ga-langre-metoo

ska du köpa något idag, så köp ett medlemskap i f!
du är det viktigaste vi har. utan dig, inget f! 
bli medlem här: https://feministisktinitiativ.se/bli-medlem/

vi minns, vi ser framåt, vi fortsätter!

#feministfriday -------- 2017 så var 99% av de som misstänktes för våldtäkt mot kvinnor män, enligt brå. när det gäller våldtäkt mot män, så var de misstänkta

nu uppmärksammar vi de delar av vår politik som har starkast koppling till bland annat vill vi : ♀ att åklagarmyndigheten och domstolsverket ges ökade resurser syfte att kvalitetshöja rättsprocessen inom sexualbrott . ♀ se en skarp lagstiftning mot könsdiskriminerande reklam , en begränsning av porr och ett förbud mot strippklubbar , för att våra offentliga rum ska vara trygga för alla . ♀ att sverige genomför informationssatsningar kring samtycke och vad den nya lagen innebär . och vi ska : ♀ verka för sexuella och reproduktiva rättigeter eu enligt svensk modell , för våra medsyskons rätt till abo och samtyckeslagstiftning . skriv uppropet om du stöttar våra politiska förslag : ska du köpa något idag , så köp ett medlemskap f ! text_retweet:
repost desde @theglobaldressmovement ♥️ 🔴 ♥️
la violencia contra la mujer es una de los problemas más álgidos en estos tiempos de la humanidad. eso ya lo sabemos. lo que queremos es ahora es dar un paso adelante y sanar.

sanar desde nosotras, con herramientas, interiormente, desde nuestra paz, desde el amor, con el poder de la autotransformación hasta sanar al ser humano sin distinción, la humanidad, el mundo, el universo.

he escuchado de un vestido que está en movimiento, en evolución, en ebullición!... he escuchado a mujeres decir "escucha a tu corazón, sigue tu intuición, sigue tu vestido"... el vestido dice "soy paz ♥️ soy amor ♥️ soy poder ♥️ soy mujer... me visto de paz, amor, mujer y poder... es el movimiento ♥️ global del vestido!... es #thedressmovement ♥️. y el movimiento se inicia contigo, conmigo, con nosotras que marcharemos el 24 de noviembre como parte de la marcha #nosotrasexigimos en la sección cultura, educación.  nos reuniremos al lado del obelisco en el campo de marte a las 3pm. iremos vestidas de #elvestidodecorazones ♥️, polos de corazones ♥️, pañuelos ♥️, bufandas ♥️, etc. o vestidas de blanco (falda o pantalón,short, etc). ¿qué haremos? <3 seremos  un grupo pacifico ♥️, amoroso ♥️ y poderoso ♥️
bailaremos en círculo ⭕️ ♥️ 🔴 y creando la cadena.
cantaremos "soy paz, soy amor, soy poder, confío en mí", el río está fluyendo, en espiral ⭕️ hacia el centro, es aquí donde quiero estar junto a ti... ♥️♥️
♥️ nos detendremos en silencio, en meditación, en contemplación.
♥️ cantaremos mantras.
♥️ disfrutaremos de diferentes danzas espontáneas.
♥️ bailaremos espontáneas, seremos y estaremos.

notas importantes: ♥️ ¡queremos que vengas con tus hijos! sentimos que es una oportunidad histórica y educativa que querrás compartir con ellos. entenderemos si tuvieras que dejar el desfile temprano para mejor servir sus necesidades.  a la discreción de cada mamá, desde su paz, su amor, y su gran poder. somos uno 🔴⭕️♥️.
♥️ pueden comprar polos, bufandas, pañuelos, vestidos de corazones a través de esta página o al whatsapp 990048889. ♥️ convoquemos a nuestros contactos para caminar juntas. todas y todos invitados!!!)
#nosotrasexigimos #thedressmovement

text:
the #metoo movement is a movement against sexual harassment and assault that has created a sea change for victims of it. now more than ever before, women are speaking up about their experiences, and perpetrators are being called upon to account for their actions. given the global nature of sexual harassment, sexual assault, and violence against women, it asks what responsibilities we have as a youth. 
let us seize this moment of opportunity marking 16 days of violence against gender based violence to create an
inclusive and diverse environment conducive to share our stories of understanding.

speak up. make your voice matter.

reach out your #metoo story. bit.ly/mymetoostory

giovedì prossimo inaugura questa 
esposizione collettiva alla quale 
ho avuto il piacere di dare il mio contributo rielaborando un manifesto storico femminista. 
in mostra ci saranno 
delle illustratrici pazzesche, 
vi consiglio di farci un salto ;) •
•
femminismi manifesti 
giovedì 29 novembre • h.18.30
c.s. bocciodromo - vicenza •
•
l'evento è stato organizzato 
da non una di meno vicenza. 
grazie @lorisfuschillo
🇬🇧
next thursday will open an exhibition 
about historical feminist posters redesigned 
by 28 illustrators. i'm glad to be part of it. 
the opening will be held at c.s. bocciodromo vicenza at 6.30 pm. thanks to loris fuschillo and non una di meno vicenza.

text:
dear 5th semester,
it's been a rollercoaster ride for me . met many lovely people , lost too . overwhelmed by all the human emotions - love, care, heartbreak, betrayal, compassion, innocence, nuisance...etc etc
but yeah it's was quite an experience. i wish another semesters goes like this . glad to meet new people, different from me in all aspects but can't ask for more. sorry to people with whom i couldn't spend time especially @tej_naren babe me olives you❤ . did so much of bakchodi , bunked classes for doing projects and assignments ( which we didn't do :p) . got screwed by teachers but who cares , we made memories . misunderstood each other but still cared for each other . 
in the beginning of this semester i never thought it will be so great , wow it was amazing . i wish we be the same untill the end of this 4 year of torturing engineering life and even after that . 
i might irritate , screw , curse , fight with you guys but from bottom of my heart love you guys alot. (ps : hate you more ❤) thank you fam
yours pshyco bro -_-

text_retweet:
taking over open society foundations’s instagram for a week with photos from my long term project 'ni una menos' on gender violence and women's movements fight for rights. 
glad to have the opportunity to give visibility on this important and current issue in the week of november 25th, the international day for the elimination of violence against women.
more info about 'ni una menos' on the website dedicated to the project www.niunamenosproject.com

#repost @opensocietyfoundations
(@get_repost)
• • •
a woman and her three daughters. after dozens of appeals to the police went unanswered, this woman separated from her abusive ex-husband. still, she cannot count on local law enforcement to protect her rights. 
despite a 2012 law which raised the maximum prison sentence for “femicide,” the killing of a woman or girl on account of her gender, argentina is still struggling against widespread gender-based violence. thankfully, a grassroots, women-led movement known as ni una menos (not one [woman] less) has arisen in argentina, and is working to empower women and defend their human rights. in this series, karl mancini (@karlitomancini) shares some of his work on the inspiring women of ni una menos and their fight for justice. to learn more about both mancini's work and ni una menos, please follow the link in our bio.

text:
november 25th is iinternational day  for the elimination of violence against women.
.
.
over the years, survivors and activists, through various campaigns such as #metoo, #timesup, #notonemore, have reached its peak. violence against women and girls cannot be and shouldn't be silenced. women and girls all over the world  are experiencing  abuse in various ways. .
.
the impact of violence is quite significant for these women and girls. women abused by their intimate partner, are 16% likely to have a low-birth-weight baby, likely to experience depression and 1.5 times likely to acquire hiv and sti.
physical, emotional and financial toll of violence sets women back from reaching their maximum potential.
.
.
#stoptheviolence #notoabuse #stopdomesticabuse 
#womenaremagic 
#eliminatetheviolence
#metoo
#timesup 
#supportasurvivor
#roslynblaize #truthingdomtheconception

text:
we’ve had enf days for gals this year..wat abt men? movember!?-where men create awareness of their health and depression by growing out their beards and moustaches? of all ladies out der, hw many of u support ur men with this🤷🏻‍♀️?
.
nw tat we’ve heard so much abt women..let’s take a moment & walk thru the journey of men..
.
he is all celebrated and welcomed to this weird world..pampered all his childhood and adolescence, by his mum..he grows up playful and naughty..everything is good until he is a boy..
.
but life changes somewhr between his canvas to leather formals, his baggy cargos to formal trousers, his cool dude swag to the gentleman looks..& by now, he has given up on his favourite subject at college, jus cz it doesn’t offer placements..his fav bike cz his parents kudn afford it..his passion, cz he needs to settle..😑😌
.
den comes - the transformation, marriage..a major ✅ on every parents’ checklist..
.
why is it tat a gal is pitied for leaving her parents..imagine a stranger claiming a share in every inch of ur space at home? isn’t it more than an *eeewwww* moment? .
as a father, he is our fav superhero who sets a benchmark to the guy we date😇as a boyfriend he crazily falls on his knees and asks us out😍as a husband he unconditionally loves❤️as a brother he protects☺️as a friend he always cares☃️as a son he shows how adventurous u can ever be😂
.
between all these #savegirlchild #metoo #womenempowerment, let’s take a moment and let the men in our lives know how special they are..for, they make this world a better and a safer place for us to live😇
.
.
dear men,
*wn u had all the choices of running away, u chose to stay..!!
*wn everything clinged on, to weigh u down, instead of a free fall, u had the strength to stand up tall..!!
*wn it all fell apart to break u down, instead of crying out loud, u made us smile..!!
*wn all u had was chaos around, u chose to give us peace..!!
.
cheers to ur strength & compassion🍻hey beautiful soul, u deserve to be celebrated🤩thanks to all those positive male role models who’ve influenced our lives🤘🏻
.
✨positive vibes ur way✨
#gratitude #love #respect #man
#photography #travel #passion #livelovelaugh #life #yatriclicks

text:
daphne is a free spirited girl who lives with her bohemian family in london, which consists of her writer father ed, an activist mother ellie and a scholarly brother theo. ed and ellie, who are too busy in their pursuits and “affairs”, do not believe in conventional parenting and want their children to find their own way in life. daphne also has a best friend jane, who is smart and mature, but at the same time desires to be what daphne is, an object of everyone’s desire. enter ralph, a musician with an inherent charm and devil may care attitude. sparks fly between daphne and ralph, and each is convinced that he/she is in love. only issue; daphne is nine and ralph is twenty-seven.

the book explores the issue of pedophilia, but not in a very didactic or pontificating tone. at no point in the narrative did i feel that the situation was such that there was a moral absolute and therefore definitely a victim party to side with. this is because the power of @sofkazinovieff writing is such that it actually almost humanized ralph’s character at times. it explored the mind of a pedophile very well; to him love was an emotion beyond the constraints of age and sex was just an act of expressing love. daphne was convinced of the same, till years later she saw the situation in a different light, when she was herself the mother of a daughter. jane’s motive for pushing daphne towards seeking justice was kept a well-guarded secret till the very end; which at many times would make the reader’s question her intentions. it also made me wonder if it is the situations and surroundings that contribute to such behavior. ed and ellie gave their children freedom, but wasn’t it also necessary for them to give them guidance and the safety net of a home. was it the “hippie rock-n-roll” culture of the seventies that just normalized this behavior?

in the end i wanted justice to be served; and this is where many readers would have been left frustrated. but may be there was catharsis to be found? comparisons of this book to lolita are inevitable; but it comes in a very different era and at a time when the fires of #metoo are blazing across the globe. it is a #mustread of 2018.
#putney

text:
대학원 면접을 보러가기 전, 나는 어떤 모습으로 면접에 가야할까 많이 고민했다. 집에 있는 정장은 모두 치마나 원피스거나 몸매의 굴곡을 부각시키는 디자인이었고, 그건 요즘의 내가 지향하는 차림새가 아니기 때문이었다.
.
그동안 면접을 보러갈때면 써클렌즈에 하이힐에 원피스는 기본이었는데, 난 그것이 여성의 면접복장이라고 배웠던 것 같다. 특히 올해 sbs 아나운서 면접을 보러갈때는 최대한 키가 커보이고 각선미가 잘 드러날만한 스킨톤의 13cm 구두를 신고 갔다. 그리고 면접을 보기 직전까지 거울을 보며 외모를 가다듬었던 기억이 난다.
.
그런 외모의 강박에서 벗어나 이번 면접에서 만큼은 [박은수]를 당당하게 평가받고 싶었다. 그게 내가 추구하는 것이고 지향하는 탈코르셋의 본질이었기 때문이다.
.
오늘 나는 셔츠에 니트를 입고 검은 바지에 운동화를 신었다. 안경을 썼으며, 화장은 일체 하지 않았다. 일상생활에서 페미니즘을 실천하기는 사실 쉽지 않다. 나 또한 머뭇거릴 때도 있다. 그렇지만, 나의 아주 사소한 작은 실천이 나를 만들고, 또 누군가에게 용기가 될 수 있을 것이라 생각한다.
name: 박은수 EunSoo Park 朴恩秀

job said "he may not come when i want him,  but he'll be there right on time!" he's an on time god, yes he is!
that’s exactly what jesus did. he didn’t make it easy for himself by avoiding people’s troubles, but waded right in and helped out. “i took on the troubles of the troubled,” is the way scripture puts it. even if it was written in scripture long ago, you can be sure it’s written for us . god wants the combination of his steady, constant calling and warm, personal counsel in scripture to come to characterize us , keeping us alert for whatever he will do next. may our dependably steady and warmly personal god develop maturity in you so that you get along with each other as well as jesus gets along with us all. then we’ll be a choir—not our voices only, but our very lives singing in harmony in a stunning anthem to the god and father of our master jesus!

text:
this #16daysofactivism remember to check in on your sisters. remember to hold them close, embrace them, remind them that they are valuable. that they are worthy of joy, laughter and light. 
every day is about fighting the ugliness with love and stretching out our hands, opening our hearts to hear the stories of others and helping them heal. 
i feel very strongly about sensationalising stories of abuse and violence, prioritising these stories and merely hashtaging #metoo without taking some time out to really create spaces where victims of abuse can be angry, sad, frustrated confused, and then talk until they come out of that darkness. it isn't enough to make these stories trend. we also need to make sure they never happen again, we can only do this through the power of sisterhood which always affirms our purpose beyond and away from situations and people that hurt us.

text:
*dolore e desiderio* “vittima dell’amore, vedo un cuore spezzato. hai una storia da raccontare.

vittima dell’amore: è una parte così facile e tu sai recitarla così bene. ...credo che tu sappia cosa intendo. stai camminando sul filo, tra dolore e desiderio, in cerca dell’amore." poesia tratta dal libro "donne che amano troppo". un libro da leggere, in qualsiasi caso, per comprendere le altre, per comprendere noi stesse. 
su igtv proverò a fare il mio primo video in cui condividerò e commenterò insieme a voi una storia tratta dal libro, una storia che parla di una donna che ha imparato dal passato e che riesce a non ricadere nel solito baratro. una storia di speranza, perché imparare ad amare se stesse e a proteggersi, evitando persone che ci faranno del male, pur essendo alla ricerca disperata di amore dagli altri, si può.
.
.
.

text:
(tw // assault & rape) #thisisnotconsent 
it's 2018. the #metoo movement is strong. women all over the world, including myself, are speaking out about their experiences with sexual assault and rape after being silenced for years. finally, finally, we feel as if we are getting somewhere. we are finally getting it through to men that they do not have a right to our bodie and our bodies will be forever ours and only ours to do what we like with.

and then, a 17 year old girl is blamed for her rape - because she was wearing the "wrong type of underwear". her lace fronted thong clearly meant she was asking for it. it is 2018, and our society is still trying to come up with ways to justify rape and sexual assault. it is 2018, and we are teaching young women to be scared to go out in even jeans and a t-shirt because they will be catcalled and wolf-whistled, being made into prey for other people to stare at. it is 2018, and we are bringing young women up being taught how not to be raped, rather than bringing our young men up being taught not to rape. it is 2018, and young women still cannot even wear pretty underwear just for ourselves without being told we are just doing it for attention. it is 2018, and we are still asking for it. it is still our fault.

i wasn't asking for it. my friends who have spoken up were not asking for it. that young, strong, gorgeous 17 year old was not asking for it. none of us were asking for it to happen to us - when will you stop trying to convince the world that we were? how many more beautiful young girls need to go through this and the subsequent embarrassment, mental and physical trauma and humiliation before you realise that our clear, resounding no, means no?

our clothing has never and will never equal our consent.

text:
melalui enam belas film festival kalian tidak hanya menonton film yang ditayangkan, tapi juga turut bersuara melawan segala jenis kekerasan yang ada di muka bumi.
.
❌hentikan kekerasan!
❤tebarkan kasih sayang
✔pada
👉siapapun❤
👉apapun❤
👉kapanpun❤
dan
👉dimanapun❤
.
enam belas film festival mulai 25 november - 10 desember 2018.
.
untuk kamu yang berdomisili di kota jakarta follow instagram enam belas film festival @enambelasffest untuk menonton film dan mengikuti ragam kegiatan menarik.
.
untuk kamu yang di kota tangerang follow instagram cinespace @cine_space untuk menonton film dan menghadiri diskusi yang diselenggarakan.
.
semua film yang ditayangkan bisa kamu tonton gratis, tapi panitia menyediakan kotak donasi, hasil dari donasi kawan-kawan akan disalurkan kepada para penyintas kekerasan.
.

text:
2018 has seen progress on many fronts for women as victims of sexual violence and abuse, particularly through the #metoo movement. but there are women fighting for their rights daily behind the scenes, and they matter too and hence #hearmetoo. 
in the days leading up to the 16 days of violence against women (25th november to 10 december), let’s start to be sensitive to all humans, let’s believe their stories, let’s stop blaming victims and let’s be wary of the words we use so that we are not perpetrators of verbal violence. 
let’s start now. 
@unwomen 
#feminism #genderequality #hearmetoo #metoo #sexualviolence #humanrights #empowerment #wedialogue #wedialoguetogether #equalityforall #loveislove #lgbtq #mencanbevictimstoo #16daysofactivism

text:
“it’s christmas party time!
free-flowing alcohol and an expectation for employees to behave is not realistic. yes, we’re adults and we’re professionals, but we’re also human and can all fall fowl of the excesses of alcohol.
we’ve all heard the horror stories of the one employee who took things too far – or perhaps even been that employee. we’ve found the evidence of the inappropriate photocopier usage, we’ve skirted the confrontation with the person with whom we couldn’t help but recount our first impressions (“i thought you were a bit of a try-hard when i first met your dave”), we’ve recoiled at the videos of our dad dancing popping up on our social media timelines the next morning. our top tip is limit the drinks vouchers.

if you do have an incident and need some support get in touch!  #gurls #workplace #woman #entrepreneur #femaleentrepreneur

text:
власний бізнес 💼 завжди передбачає серйозні ризики💥🔥 💡створення своєї справи – досить проста процедура, але розвиток і підтримання рентабельності підприємства 📈 - це складна і довготривала праця,  впоратися з якою вдається небагатьом.
навіть при наявності стабільного рівня прибутковості бізнесу💰, вся справа може зазнати краху під впливом обставин, яким ми іноді не приділяємо уваги❕.
.
📜процедура страхування комерційного майна, що належить підприємствам і компаніям, дає гарантію захисту від різних непередбачуваних ситуацій, істотно зменшуючи ризик втрати всього бізнесу.
.
договір страхування майна юридичних осіб передбачає захист ⬇ :
.
☔конструкції будівель, споруд та приміщень разом з оздобленням та скляними елементами;
.
🌂обладнання, в тому числі виробничого, торгового, побутової та офісної техніка;
.
☔товарних запасів, в тому числі сировини та готової продукції;
.
🌂меблі, та інше майно.⠀
.
покриваючи такі страхові ризики ⏬:
.
🔹пожежа🔥;
.
🔹вибух 💥;
.
🔹затоплення⠀💦;
.
🔹протиправні дії третіх осіб🚨;
.
🔹стіхійні лиха⚡💧;
.
🔹відповідальність за заподіяння шкоди третім особам при експлуатації об'єкта нерухомості 🏡🛃.
.
страховик надає фінансову допомогу💸 тільки якщо підприємство не винне в псуванні комерційної нерухомості, техніки, обладнання або  іншого майна. навіть недбале відношення до правил безпеки не дозволяє отримати матеріальної допомоги. .

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
"if married, we're called aunty.
if single, it's lame.
if unmarried it's shame...shame.
to quote shakespeare:
"what's in a name?"
why do you play this game of surnames?
if i study a lot,then....."hey nerd"
if i use too much lipstick,then..."hey heroine"
if i reach home late,you doubt my character.
all i want to say,
"where the hell are my rights?"
whether it's size zero or xxl,
it's our lives, so what the hell
let go of the taunts,
that's what women want.
to be,to live,to love...
stay quite or just flaunt!! " -kareena kapoor khan

kareena kapoor khan made a poetic pitch for women's rights at the launch of her maiden radio show:what women want.

text:
the man in image 1 is a maintenance boy alleged to have masterbated in a lift in front of a 2nd year student of srm university, kattankulatur, chennai when this gross behaviour was informed to the administration, they turned a blind eye and gave reluctant response to the victim. they blamed her being a girl from north india studying in south which led her face this. they also threatened that they know about girls doing alcohol and cigarettes in hostels. this sort of discrimination and orthodox attitude makes the administration an acquaintance in the crime as well. what followed were series of protests not very commonly seen in private universities. 
as of now, the maintenance boy has not been traced after the incident. as the administration is answerable and accountable to the deeds of the man and those who took the incident lightly,  one question must pertain, "are women really safe in campuses albeit the restrictions imposed on them ?" @pinjratod 
#srmuniversity #metoo #molestationawareness #protest #chennai.
.

text: "when i jumped off the cliff all by myself in bringing a sexual harassment lawsuit against my boss at fox news, there was no #metoo movement or times up pins. it was just me, all alone, taking on one of the most powerful men in the world. and my children were my paramount concern. how would they fare? how would they be treated? would they be ok? turns out i underestimated them. just three months after my resolution was announced, it was the first day of school and i was really nervous. but kaia, came home and said, “mom, a lot of people asked me about you today and what happened to you over the summer… and mommy… i was so proud to say you were my mom.” @therealgretchencarlson talks us through the moment she pioneered the #metoo movement and gave women worldwide, including her daughter, the courage to find their own voices. read our exclusive story with the inspiring mother of two and american tv news veteran on the site now under ‘profiles’✨✨✨

text:
despite the fact that ethlyne clair (born november 23, 1904) was probably one of the most beautiful women ever to grace the screen during the late 1920s/early 1930s, she never became a star.
•
ethlyne made her break for stardom after winning a beauty contest in her home town of talladega, alabama, and headed to new york to find work as an extra (her first role of note was in sandra (1924) starring barbara la marr). •
•
in hollywood, she signed a contract with universal; appearing in a handful of comedies shorts, including the newlyweds, followed by a spate of westerns opposite hoot gibson. •
•
in 1928, she married her agent, richard lonsdale hinshaw, in mexico. it was an unhappy union; she later revealed he forced her into marriage at gunpoint. her career also waned, after playing second fiddle to rex, the wonder horse, she left universal, and freelanced. it was pathé, representing a variety of independent film studios, who nominated her as one of the years wampas baby stars of 1929. the accolade kept her in the press; she was also one of hollywood’s first stars to launch her own beauty care range. it was this which brought her to the attention of ernest westmore, of the hollywood make-up dynasty.
•
divorced from her husband, her marriage to ernest wasn’t without drama; when at their wedding, his first wife showed up with their daughter, muriel, dressed in rags to highlight the state of poverty ernest had left them in. ernest in turn flew at photographers; got into a brawl and was arrested. as his career flourished, ethlyne’s went into a deep decline; her temporary contract with warner bros. had expired and she was out of work. later, in 1991, she claimed that mogul daryl zanuck ruined her career after she refused his sexual advances. •
•
by 1934, with her film career over, she tried her hand on the stage with limited results. instead, divorced from ernest, she married again, to a second-hand car salesman, and retired to raise her family. she died in february 1996, aged 91.
•
•

bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
there is an exciting movement happening at present where conversations, previously shunned, are being welcomed and celebrated. men and women are finding themselves - women discovering a strength that they had historically suppressed and men a vulnerability - due to unwritten societal rules
.
whilst this movement is revolutionary, it is bringing with it a sense of unease and uncertainty experienced more so by men. historically men have been depicted as pillars of strength, power, leadership and as providers in society. thankfully in the millennial era we understand that there is nothing tougher or more resilient than being vulnerable
.
life affects us all, financial worries, relationship breakdowns, grief, stress, joy, babies, marriage, affairs etc etc happen to men and women and there is no right or wrong way to respond. we all have the same emotional needs and we must all work to create a society where everyone can open up and feel how they want to feel without judgement
.
with the highest rate of suicide, mental health problems and illicit drug and alcohol abuse, men are struggling to cope. the stats are shocking and it is the duty of all to show encouragement and support for men to be true to themselves
.
november is an important month because it raises awareness of issues affecting men specifically, but we must all be mindful and extend our gratitude, celebration and protection of men and their wellbeing always.
.
some key messages for men especially:
it’s ok to not be ok but it’s not ok to not get help for it. don’t suffer in silence.
.
more men than you would ever imagine are going through the same stressors, opening up will let them open up too. connection is key.
.
worrying signs : sad all the time, tired all the time, not sleeping, over-sleeping, loss of appetite, unable to enjoy things previously loved, reduced libido, feelings of hopelessness, suicide, self harm - any of these, go see your gp asap. .
wellness is gender-neutral. our health is our single most valuable asset, we must protect it and help others understand the value of their wellbeing too. .
#menshealth #yourlifestyledoctors #healthawareness #mentalhealth #wellbeing #wellness #health #life

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

tahun ini kali kedua kita menyelenggarakan enam belas film festival.
kami percaya bahwa pemulihan korban serta penanggulangan kekerasan seksual dapat kita lakukan jika seluruh masyarakat indonesia mampu menyadari bahwa kekerasan seksual harus kita akhiri.
.
untuk melanjutkan upaya dari perjuangan tersebut, kami pun kembali berkontribusi dengan mengadakan penayangan 16 film panjang, pendek, dan dokumenter karya anak bangsa yang mampu memicu mulainya pembicaraan mengenai kekerasan seksual. maraknya kasus demi kasus sepanjang tahun 2017-2018, membuat kita untuk semakin peduli dan turut andil dalam menghentikan kekerasan!
.
tertarik datang? follow instagram @enambelasffest untuk lihat jadwal tayang film, diskusi dan banyak acara menarik lainya.😘
.

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
.
🌹divine feminine 👸👸🏾
.
the other day, i had a fine debate about the #metoo movement with a group of young amazing ladies.
.
if you knew my personal story, you would also know why i strongly stand for women’s right to be treated with dignity and respect. 🙏
.
however, i also strongly believe that it’s crucial to let go of our anger. 😌
.
holding onto a resentment is like
🔥 « drinking a poison and waiting for the other person to die »🔥
ask my asthma, we have few agonising stories that are proving this point.
.
here what i have learned. 
no matter what you’ve been through,
💫 one can touch your body but nobody can touch your soul. 💫
.
so instead of thinking “i am a soiled body stuck with memories of hurt”, keep telling yourself
😇 “i am an unbreakable soul and i’m graced with an infinite power”. 😇
.
you’ll become an inspiring role model and an influential leader. 💪🏼
.
you will lead your life, your company, your community, you will inspire and appease your family with your calmness and clarity, with your kindness and creativity, with your intuition and wisdom. 👊🏻💪🏼✌🏽
.
instead of being stuck with anger or fear
🌟 unleash your divine feminine. 🌟
.
.
.
.
.
.
#metoomovement#hurted#victim#stuckinlove#womenempowerment#respectwomen#dignity#selfempowerment#millennials#themillennialshif

text:
milkman is a flipping masterpiece.  it's such a magnificent read (clever, funny, haunting, devastating) and so timely given today's discussions on both the precariousness of the good friday agreement and male sexual entitlement (two of the main themes of this book.) on a personal level, while not anywhere near as serious as ni, i grew up in a small scottish town rife with sectarian divisions. this book articulates so many experiences i've had and never been able to articulate properly. 
but if you've no knowledge of that area 
this is a timeless book that would appeal to anyone who's felt limited by the weight of place, culture and gossip. 
a totally worthy winner of the @manbookerprize2018 #milkman #annaburns #manbookerprize #metoo

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

anxiety can impact physical and mental health. there are short- and long-term effects on both the mind and body.
while many people know about the effects of anxiety on mental health, fewer people are aware of the physical side effects, which can include digestive issues and an increased risk of infection. anxiety can also change the function of the cardiovascular, urinary, and respiratory systems.

text:
друзья, как вы думаете - почему я так много транслирую информацию о детях? да потому что меня это просто прёт!

мы с тохой растим классного и любимого мишаню - и по первой вся детская тема была просто актуальна - не более.

но сейчас это то, чем я живу! знаете, ради этого я готова встать в 6 утра и через день сменять утренние тренировки - например, крутыми и полезными книгами о детстве, изучать - и делиться этим с вами.

проводя консультации со взрослыми, я сталкиваюсь с разными проблемами. но корнями все они часто упираются в детство - прямо или косвенно, в виде сценарий и заготовок - наше детство сформировало нас, сегодняшних, ярких и классных - со своими фишками и заморочками.

поэтому я вижу супер важность и нужность этой темы сегодня. спамлю в стори, провожу тренинги и много, много об этом говорю 💕

включайтесь и присоединяйтесь! виз лав.

#psychology #instamamru_cheb #cheboksary #инстамама #детскаяпсихология

поэтому я вижу супер важность и нужность этой темы сегодня. спамлю в стори, провожу тренинги и много, много об этом говорю 💕

включайтесь и присоединяйтесь! виз лав.
