text:
(3/3)
as someone who travels alone extensively, iran was rough to navigate as a woman alone, not in a tour group, not with a male partner or companion, not being taxied about from one perfect sight directly to another perfect site and staying by the picturesque reflection pool of a beautifully maintained guest house half the day. a lot of the time, out on the streets and in the less touristy bazaars and sitting in popular parks, there were iranian women and men of all ages who were openly hostile toward a young woman alone. it was incredibly hard and doing workaway toward the end of my month in iran was what saved me.

my experience had been turned around nearly 180 degrees and i met the most amazing iranians and fellow travellers who all changed not just my trip but my life.

it has take me a long time to be able to sit with my trauma and i'm now ready to speak about my experiences and the beautiful people i met, not without also acknowledging the really difficult times.

text:
🚨attention all women 🚨
i’m writing a book about what it’s like to be a woman in these changing times and what we can do to continue moving things forward towards equality for all of us. i want to inspire not only all of us, but also the younger generation to never give up the amazing work that’s already been started. and, i want to feature real women’s stories within it!
- what have been your experiences as a girl and woman?
- have you found yourself in situations of being controlled, discriminated, abused, or objectified because of your gender?
- when did you realise that things had to change and what are you doing to help yourself and others?
-what would you like the younger generation to know, and what do we all need to keep fighting for?

don’t think you don’t have a story to tell; we all do. we’ve all been through things that should make us angry and hungry for change. if you’d like the chance to be featured in my book, send your story and details to kateoman@yahoo.co.uk
i want to give you a voice. i want to help shine a light on the abuse of the patriarchy, and how real women like you are all saying it’s time up on that bs 💪🏻🚺🔥#yourstory #ourstory #patriarchy #feminism #timesup #metoo #womenstandtogether

text:
[ tribune ] #2 ✍ • que reste-t-il de nos ideaux ? •
- extrait -
•
#metoo. il y a un an, une autopsie encore inédite de la société s’emparait en temps réel de la toile. au scalpel, les vérités sont ressorties, une à une,  de la mémoire des femmes. des survivantes, dont les témoignages sur la violence subie, n’ont laissé plus aucun doute sur leur condition. insultes, harcèlement, violences gynécologiques, viols, lesbophobie, transphobie, agressions, persécutions, mutilations, menaces, humiliations, racisme, inceste, discriminations : autant de mots et leurs maux ont emporté dans leur mouvement un voile. ce voile des apparences, qui cachait, depuis bien trop longtemps, le vice de forme d’une société dite des droits humains. 
des violences sexistes et sexuelles qui continuent de n’épargner, encore à l’heure actuelle, aucun milieu ni aucune femme. mes dernières rencontres pour les ambitieuses en témoignent et en témoigneront encore, sans doute. a la différence peut être, que cette vague 2.0 a permis d’encourager les victimes de violence, à s’en « libérer » et (ré)agir en fonction.

le paradigme d’une société à deux vitesses
sauf qu’il reste aujourd’hui, des paramètres à bousculer et faire évoluer pour changer définitivement le paradigme de la société. un an plus tard, les facteurs (institutionnels ou individuels) qui empêchent les femmes et les filles d'exercer leurs droits fondamentaux comme leur combat d’avancer, sont toujours aussi vifs et multiples. des derniers faits d’actualité comme certaines prises de paroles rapportées, montrent sensiblement une confusion ou un mépris aussi lourd de sens que la main trop insistante d’un homme sur le genou d’une femme.

et si au-delà de ces voix tortueuses qui divisent, (...)

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
i saw this and had to post it, while social media doesn't help with mental health, it feels like an escape from going to school and everyday life, so i can totally understand. school seriously has caused me to have a lot of symptoms of anxiety and depression, and my parents still don't believe me and just tell me to get off my phone and go outside and ill be happy. like that's not how it works, it might help a bit but it doesn't solve anything because the main problem is the pressure to get good grades and the pressure our teachers put on us by being horrible a lot of the time. ~🍑🌻

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text: some people still aren't getting the memo so let me break it down quickly: body positivity is about respect. not who you find attractive or not. not who you think is healthy or not. all bodies deserve respect because they hold human beings. no exceptions. the amount of body shaming and cyber bullying on my feed today makes me feel nauseous. literally. i'd prefer a woman taking selfies that society would label as narcissistic, over a woman who doesn't think she's beautiful... every. time. its harder to love and accept yourself in a world designed to make you feel, "without". so if some womans sexy selfie bugs you, scroll the f🦄ck on and leave her alone. you ain't gotta say shit.✋ #selflove #bodypositive #mybody #metoo #healthy #mentalhealthawareness

this is an original i was recording or more precisely had to write and record although i was having swollen vocal chords. what was such an urgency you ask? then the answer is myental space. i had to put out the chaos by any means.
i am the person who believes that diseases are simply energy defficiency and disorders. specifically i believed that mental disorders arent actually treated by medication rather one has to heal themselves. but my perception changed when i went through two to three phases of those downward spirals..which were i don't know caused by what. i realized that once you are down there in your own mind's created darkness, it's really hard to be strong and get up and look after your own self. although that's the only true  solution, but to reach the solution you need a ladder of medication maybe or some sort of talk. 
in this era of money and recognition don't loose yourself to your work ...whatever you become you will attract, so don't just down if you are depressed, talk it out, always have a company that will listen to you. and don't ever be afraid to tell that's the only ladder which could actually get you to sanity and self love 
talk it out .
.
.

text:
today is white ribbon day, a day australia is asked to reflect, remember and prevent all violence against women! 
yet today, despite this message, we mourn the loss of yet another beautiful soul, emily miller, who was yesterday shot and killed by her male partner; leaving behind 4 children, all under the age of 10.

her death brings the tally of australian women murdered this year to 72!! ⁣⁣🆘‼️ people, listen to the facts!! 📣domestic violence and abuse in australia is only increasing!
🔺when will these numbers alarm australians to acknowledge that this is actually a more prominent threat of terrorism?!
🔺when will the statistics hit home strong enough for action and prevention to be the priority for change?
🔺when will live solutions become part of the discussion to improve public safety?
🔺when will we realise that we are not doing enough, because not enough of us are doing!! -
i hear the chants: “violence against women, australia says no!” ❌
-well i say, “prove it!” .
#domesticviolence #raisingawareness #abuse #familyviolence #deathtollrising #violenceagainstwomen

text:
i fail all the time.
i try to be a teacher, a role model, a beacon of light to everyone i meet.
of course, i'm young but age is not a measurement of wisdom

i have done things i'm ashamed of.
i have hurt people. i have hurt myself. i feel like i should have died from the power of my own self hatred 
i was alone and hurting. seeking any kind of guidance. i didn't find peace in religion like everyone else seems to find. 
i want to help people realize there's more to life than exams, bills, popularity, and any other sources of stress.

you deserve love. 
self love is what saved me from my darkest thoughts.

i urge you reading this, whoever you are, please to learn to truly love yourself. "darkness cannot drive out darkness, only light can do that. hate cannot drive out hate, only love can do that." love is the most powerful emotion. every living being deserves love. i hope you learn to truly love everything around you. when you do your life will be transformed

learn from past mistakes. that's what this page is for. i hope maybe one day this reaches someone who needs it. my dms are always open to anyone who needs someone to talk to. stay strong and love

#starwars #thelastjedi #yoda #jedi #jedimaster #quotes #mlk #love #selflove #blacklivesmatter  #lgbt #lgbtq #theforceawakens #soloastarwarsstory #metoo

i want to help people realize there's more to life than exams, bills, popularity, and any other sources of stress.

you deserve love. 
self love is what saved me from my darkest thoughts.

i urge you reading this, whoever you are, please to learn to truly love yourself. "darkness cannot drive out darkness, only light can do that. hate cannot drive out hate, only love can do that." love is the most powerful emotion. every living being deserves love. i hope you learn to truly love everything around you. when you do your life will be transformed

learn from past mistakes. that's what this page is for. i hope maybe one day this reaches someone who needs it. my dms are always open to anyone who needs someone to talk to. stay strong and love

text:
-- i think it's so bizarre that i've gotten so much push back about my work (the neuropsychology of whiteness) from my creepy as fuck publisher to getting my posts deleted on ig ...even though i don't even have followers like that (really, calm down instagram) when there are *literally articles* with cover art featuring a massive sweep of blond hair *swallowing* perception-oriented facial orifices (eyes, ears, nose...) wild .

i think it's basically because i'm black and my dads rich and my mothers white (that they way i personally identify), and people just want me to be white washed bc it's more comfortable for everyone ...else
.

im keeping a peripheral analog about it as i go forth, bc im just not stopping any time soon. and frankly, it's just not that offensive. what is offensive? the 80% of racists, most of whom pretend not to know
.

and i just fucking love this photo, particularly with the little flower, as if it's a "blind as a fucking bat" cultural hairdo. like, white girl in her 60s walks into a salon like, "i want the 'culturally ignorant for life' style. i have a #metoo gala tonight"
.

and all i actually study at this point is american white people talking to other american white people about the psychology of american white people, so for each pairing? i love one (typically the author) and just study the other
.

white trash meg the food photographer and meg newman are *adjacent* to my work, though i *have* tossed both legal cases around in class bc *what the fuck were either of them thinking?* oh, absolutely nothing beyond their whitness, particularly white trash meg bc we *actually have* visual evidence, eye witnesses and audio, and like, 300 emails... and she committed an actual felony (when she tried to repurpose the narrative and preform an inauthentic innocence) and lied to the *court* ...smh. but this *massive amount* of white girl hysteria is being carefully categorized by me bc anecdotal tails are interesting, but it's professionally inappropriate to factor my own shit in .

im too black for that; it actually fucks up the objectivity necessary to cast the net as wide as it needs to be
.

short story:

domestic violence and abuse in australia is only increasing! 🆘
.

-well i say, “prove it!” .

text:
[please read] today was rough and i am reaching out to this wonderful community for advice. 
coming from an extremely conservative household and family, simply my presence in a space with my conservative family members is tense. fortunately, it only occurs 2x a year, on the holidays. my family is very small, so when tensions run high or conversations get heated, sides are taken quickly and it always ends up being me vs the rest of the people in the room. 
today, my uncle had the audacity to say that women in college are “ruining men’s lives” by “crying rape” when they just “regretted having sex and weren’t mature enough to handle those emotions.” he said that these men were “suffering” because of the women that “pointed the finger” at them and that these men’s lives were “ruined forever.” after this and much more victim blaming, i had to get up and remove myself from the toxic and dangerous space, however, i remained silent. in any other situation i would’ve spoken up and welcomed the debate. i would not have rested until he understood why he was wrong. 
as a rape survivor i should’ve spoken up. i should’ve defended myself and my fellow sisters. i’m angry at myself that i did not. and for what reason? to make sure everyone else in the room wasn’t uncomfortable? it’s bullshit and i’m sick and tired of my family dynamics bullying me into submission. how do you all handle these situations? i need guidance. thank you in advance.

text:
i am practicing self love.

it's taken me a long time to learn to love and accept myself...especially my hair. coming from a mixed background has sometimes made me feel like i dont belong to a specific culture or group.

tonight at yoga, i reflected on the fact that this has really been the year of self love and priority for me. it's both lovely and overwhelming. after years of being in an abusive relationship, i found my joy, confidence and self esteem really plummeted.

but now i'm rebuilding and celebrating me. this is a really monumental phase on the healing journey. i'm happy to be here, and i hope my story will encourage you in your own.

still a queen 👑✊.
.
.
.

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

today, friday 23 november, is nationally known as white ribbon day.  throughout the year, and in particular the last week and today, i have dedicated my time and energy to my advocacy duties for @whiteribbonaust in my appointed role as white ribbon advocate. 
i am a domestic violence survivor and living proof that there can be life after domestic violence. i am proud and honoured to be part of part a global movement working to end men’s violence against women. through my ambassadorial and advocacy work, i aim to create a society where all women can live in safety, free from violence and abuse. 🙏🏻❤️

text:
this thanksgiving i sat back to reflect on all the things in my life that i’m thankful for, and how many things i have experienced thus far. .
i have tremendous gratitude for all the universe has blessed me with, for both the struggles and the dark times as well as the abundance.  i’ve learned so much about myself and learned how strong i really am. i’ve had to overcome some really tough things over the past 5 years ... things that i have kept private and suffered in silence. no more . it’s time i speak my truth. i’ve survived a vicious physical attack, one so horrific and demoralizing and many other attacks on me, and my professionalism in my position at work by some really miserable jealous and desperate people, but the point is that i overcame them , stronger then ever before.
i didn’t understand why i had to go through this when i was going through the hardest times in my life, over these past 5 years. the #universe makes no mistakes. i had these experiences because i now understand after lots and lots of work, i needed them to grow in order to become the person i am becoming. i could never speak like this, and of these traumas publicly before. i suffered in silence. after suffering a complete mental breakdown, i fought hard for 2 years to overcome my depression, anxiety and ptsd from these traumas. over the past 2 years, i’ve learned that speaking my truth and showing #vulnerability does not in any way or form mean weakness. it means strength. super human strength. #unfuckwithable strength. .
i courageously walked away from my career and began a new one . i walked away from toxicity, jealousy and everything and everyone that sucked the spirit and soul out of me. i also walked away from the same career that i loved and people that i loved . it was difficult but in the end... i chose me. i had to love myself enough and put myself.. my sanity and my life first.
i now choose to speak about being brutally attacked because if there is one woman out there suffering in shame and in silence, i want to sit beside her and hold her hand. i want  her to know that one day she too will overcome her pain and she’s not alone and she too has super human strength .

text:
an older picture i took after the second move out. so life has been difficult lately. i'm trying to deal with it but i've been rather silent at least on this side of the instagram. but, i wanted to take a moment and say how i much i appreciate you all. you're all loved. if you ever need to talk, i'm here. you may feel alone sometimes, but honestly, we all do. as humans we liked to give the appearance of having everything together when we are actually struggling and/or feeling incredibly alone. and, this silly notion that we have to get through everything alone on the basis of us being functional-adult humans is what causes so much unnecessary suffering and mental illnesses. it's okay to talk you guys. so if you need to talk (even if you're an unknown stranger here on ig) there's always someone who will listen. even for friends and family, if i can't help or listen, there is someone who can. you just need to be open to finding them and look for them. 
love to you all, 
kaila 💫

text: i still remember the hopeful energy from the warm air of a summer evening in manhattan. that energy that pushed me out of my comfort zone, encouraged me to meet new people, a risk i rarely take. i still remember the disappointment when i wasn’t seen, and worse, when i finally was acknowledged only to discover i had been forgotten. adult me recoiled into my former preteen self; unworthy, invisible, silenced. i still remember the way the sour in my stomach, that i’ve come to quickly identify as shame, was instantly soothed when charlotte stood up for me, reclaiming my seat at the table just when i had so easily given it up. 🙋🏻‍♀️ if you’ve ever been made to feel invisible and find yourself constantly battling that inner narrative that tells you, ‘you don’t deserve to be here’, remember that you have the agency to stand up for yourself. more importantly, remember that you have the power to speak up for others when you sense that their own shame is keeping them quiet. because it was only when charlotte spoke up for me that i realized i did deserve to be heard, seen and present. the silenced cannot make space for themselves, we must put aside our resentment for the privileges we lack and use the ones we do have to lift each other up. 💪🏽 so today i’m thankful for new york city; for teaching me that i deserve to be seen and heard, for encouraging me to be assertive, and showing me how to carve space for myself. and i’m thankful for women like @charlottenoelle_ who lead by example.

text: photo by @rosebaca | let us tell you about someone you probably know nothing about — but you should. her name is adlene harrison, and she was the first woman to be mayor of dallas. "at age 95, she is as feisty — and at times ornery — as she was the day she walked into city hall," according to columnist sharon grigsby, who spoke with her recently. a political outsider, harrison served on the city council from 1973 to 1977. she wore her non-establishment label proudly. when asked about the “firsts” attributed to her — first female mayor in dallas, first jewish woman to serve as mayor of a major u.s. city — she grimaced. “i don’t know that that changed my life or anybody else’s. but it did say to other women, ‘go out there and run for office and do the best you can.’" so is harrison an advocate of the #metoo movement? again, gruff, no-nonsense adlene: “i hate to tell you this, but i don’t even think that much about the metoo movement. i just think about movement — i don’t care how it comes.” harrison’s experience in politics was different than that of other women who have accused powerful men of misconduct. but the trailblazer now fears too much division between the sexes. “i’ve always had a lot of help from men, and i’ll always remember what that help was.”
name: The Dallas Morning News

text:
this is an original i was recording or more precisely had to write and record although i was having swollen vocal chords. what was such an urgency you ask? then the answer is mental space. i had to put out the chaos by any means.
i am the person who believes that diseases are simply energy defficiency and disorders. specifically i believed that mental disorders arent actually treated by medication rather one has to heal themselves. but my perception changed when i went through two to three phases of those downward spirals..which were i don't know caused by what. i realized that once you are down there in your own mind's created darkness, it's really hard to be strong and get up and look after your own self. although that is the only true  solution, but to reach the solution you need a ladder of medication maybe or some sort of talk. 
in this era of money and recognition don't loose yourself to your work or society or some situation...whatever you become is what you will attract, so don't just sit down and drag your life if you are depressed, talk it out, always have a company that will listen to you, i will listen if there is no body whom you could talk to. and don't ever be afraid to tell that's the only ladder which could actually get you to sanity and self love 
talk it out .
.
.

text:
happy white ribbon day. ⁣⁣
⁣a thirty-year-old victorian woman has been shot and killed by her boyfriend. ⁣⁣
⁣her name was emily miller. ⁣⁣
she leaves behind four children under ten. ⁣
her death brings the tally of women murdered by men this year to 61. ⁣⁣
of this number, 41 women were murdered by a male intimate partner. ⁣
[ we apologise for the binary gender expression of this data, it is not acceptable to erase trans and enby folk, but currently police do not represent victims more accurately. ]⁣⁣
when will these numbers alarm australians?⁣⁣⁣
when will the statistics hit home?⁣⁣
when will we realise we aren’t doing enough?⁣⁣
thank you to @impactforwomen for keeping up-to-date records of this heartbreaking data. ⁣⁣
you can find the tally here:⁣⁣
http://www.impactforwomen.org.au/death-toll-of-violence-in-australia-2018.html⁣⁣

text:
for many people, art is not only for self-expression, but also a powerful tool to speak up about the pressing issues in our society, namely violence against gender and sexuality.

it is an issue we are all familiar with, yet we don't talk about enough. we tend to shy away when we talk about violence, be it when it comes to ourselves or other people who experienced it. this coming #16daysofactivism, we hope to open a safe space to tell stories, engage in conversations, and become part of a better change.

i am humbled to be a part of @enambelasffest in telling a story about una, a survivor of abuse as a child, and her confrontation with her abuser in #jpacblackbird.

come along and enjoy the stories in the festival and #hearmetoo at #enambelasffest!

#fightsexualviolence #fightgenderbasedviolence #equality #metoo #intersectionality #actorslife #sopranogadungan #blackbird #davidharrower
name: Ajeng Sharfina Adiwidya
tweet_full:
for many people, art is not only for self-expression, but also a powerful tool to speak up about the pressing issues in our society, namely violence against gender and sexuality.

it is an issue we are all familiar with, yet we do not talk about enough. we tend to shy away when we talk about violence, be it when it comes to ourselves or other people who experienced it. this coming #16daysofactivism, we hope to open a safe space to tell stories, engage in conversations, and become part of a better change.

text:
when i was four,
my pants were pulled down,
and my uncle pushed himself in, behind closed doors.
i didn't say anything.
i knew no one would believe. 
when i was eight,
my neighbour made me touch her parts
promising me the chocolate she kept as bait. 
i didn't say anything. 
i knew no one would believe me. ............................ we often find these words to have a female voice. but lately many men have openly voiced the same. and it is time we hear them out!
watch #hijabininja 's new video.

text:
.. it’s just art 🖋..
• once a wise woman said: now you can get upset •
@helen_diel das hab ich mir gemerkt 😜
.
.
why actually not posting this? 
on the one hand i often catch myself being upset by some kind of pics, of girls i know in real life. {and yes, it mostly depends on girlaccounts, isn’t it?} on the other hand i do like many posts, which show the work of really good photographers or sketches from great artists, which show nude figures. also many selfies of great personalities, like @yaenniverfromtheblock. what’s the difference? 
in my opinion the main reason i do this post today is to honour the great artwork of the tattooartists. 
@valeria_kapan_art @lovely_pain_tattoo_hammelburg 
i belive we do worry too much if a picture screams „i need attention“, if it’s sexual, if it’s too provocative to boys and most of all „what do others think about?“ a big problem of our society, is blaming girls for being theirselves, ‘coz somebody decided that this behaviour means „i like to have sex“ as well as „i‘m an easy lay“. what about the boyposts, halfnaked, running around instagram? no one ever waste a thought about that! can you tell me why? 
today i was just in the mood of posting art. that‘s what i was thinking of and for me that‘s the only thing that matters.
.
.
#myenglischmaybenottheyellowfromtheegg
#wortzumdonnerstag

text: happy gratitoodle. been thinking far too much,...obviously. finally starting to feel better, not complaining just being honest, my ptsd has semi calmed down and i feel like i'm not tripping balls in interactions with others for the first time in 14 months, still alright with all the drive that happened. happy to have reached this point stayed true to myself and accomplished an over a decade long mission. been thinking about the kids in cages, it's painful to reflect on. i turned out ok, though to be honest those kids definetly no matter long they sit. not saying i'm giving up but the damage to them has already gone too far. whether they be released yesterday, or tomorrow, they're gonna be the ones society never accepts, no matter how hard they try, how nice, how tolerant, how smart, how helpful, if they survive without being offed or offing themselves due to inability to relate. being raised on love is different than being raised to survive. i'm happy for the friends i do know, the people i meet that are committing a radical act being themselves in a world where so many aren't. it's an honor to be exposed to any, so few, of genuine humanness, those are the people to fight for, to live for. #freepress #metoo #blacklivesmatter #waterprotectors #grateful #thankstonotthemanyjustthefew

text: two weeks ago i started this.... ‘coffee & chat’ catch ups for survivors of childhood sexual abuse! every week, we will meet, face to face visually see we are not alone!! together we are standing up, standing tall, being proud of who we are!!! the plan is, in a few months once we are well established to change venues, invite professionals or practitioners along. we will teach make up application, hairstyling, styling, have life coaching, have fitness advice. learning to look in the mirror & love what you see again!!! #metoo #believesurvivors #makingchanges #makingadifference #gettingoutthere #creatinganamyofwarriors #fightingback

text:
i just want it to be known that this is the exact outfit i was wearing this morning when some random man twice my age decided to go out of his way and make innapropriate sexual comments about my appearance. 
i’m not normally one for posting things of this nature on social media, but honestly if i don’t use the voice i have to call out scary and disgusting acts, it just lets this sort of behaviour happen again and again. 
i was sitting in my car on the way to the office when some man in the car next to me kept rolling down his window at the lights acting like he had to tell me something. after 3 sets of lights, i finally wound my window down to see if maybe there was something wrong only to be told “i’m sorry but you caught my attention, i cannot stop looking at your thighs in those tights”. on what planet does any female just trying to make their way to work ask for these sorts of comments?! after rolling my window back up in horror, the man proceeded to start yelling abuse at me and then changed lanes behind my car as i was driving. i thought he was going to follow me to work, it was terrifying. 
this is not okay and i cannot believe that i felt embarrassed about what i was wearing as a result of his comments. 
every day sexual harassment is a thing. sometimes it’s more subtle with slight sexual innuendos. but other times it’s overt and aggressive and absolutely terrifying. 
i deserve to feel safe driving to work in my own car in the morning and not feel like i should be driving with my doors locked at all times.
so often when moments like this occur, we’re made to feel like this is our fault and they we did something to bring on this sort of attention. i just want to say that any woman sitting in her car, listening to a podcast and just trying to get to work does not ever want this sort of attention. it’s not flattering, it’s scary and it needs to end.
#metoo #metoomovement

text:
grateful everyday. for every moment. every breath. every wrong turn that led to every ounce of unexpected pain and adventure. the cracks we can’t hide that display us as never not broken. it’s through these cracks where we allow our true selves to shine. 🍁
taking a step back to recognize the blessings in our lives shouldn’t be something that happens but once a year. 🍁
stop withholding your joy. tell the people in your life that you love them. forgive those who have hurt you. they were in pain too. pick up the phone and call your parents, or your best friend who lives across the country. lean into what scares you because you’re worth having it. give to those who need help in this life because they weren’t born with the same privilege that you were. stand up and speak up for your brothers and sisters and non-binary friends who are bipoc and/or lgbtq. believe her. and keep believing in a world where we are all seen and all of our voices are heard. and love just a little bit more. 🍁
happy thanksgiving to all of you, friends. 🍁🙏🏼 photo @shockmedianyc

stop withholding your joy. tell the people in your life that you love them. forgive those who have hurt you. they were in pain too. pick up the phone and call your parents, or your best friend who lives across the country. lean into what scares you because you’re worth having it. give to those who need help in this life because they weren’t born with the same privilege that you were. stand up and speak up for your brothers and sisters and non-binary friends who are bipoc and/or lgbtq. believe her. and keep believing in a world where we are all seen and all of our voices are heard. and love just a little bit more. 🍁
happy thanksgiving to all of you, friends. 🍁🙏🏼 photo @shockmedianyc

text: every year i volunteer at schoolies week and every year i am increasingly impressed by how awesome today’s young people are. high school, and adolescence, has always been tough but now throw in increasing academic pressures, social media, rising depression and anxiety, rising stis, #metoo, and a whole bunch more. these young people absolutely deserve the opportunity to let their hair down and our job as adults it to support them to minimise harm. people often ask me why i volunteer each year and the answer is simple, there are people who sit at home and complain about the youth of today and people who get out there and get the amazing opportunity of seeing just how fantastic the youth of today are. #sexologist #hope #future #party #allyoungonce #youth #goldcoast

text:
gratitude makes everything grow 🌻 there is so much i am grateful for - a god who loves me unconditionally, my incredible husband, a family who cares about me, my 7 nieces and nephews, a church who is on fire for christ, my crossfit community/family and the ability to exercise my body, an amazing job where i can work from anywhere with my husband, the ability to to do what i love - studying to become a dietitian, my beneath the surface family and all your encouragement to keep going. i’m thankful for the simple things also - like nathan jokingly getting down on one knee yesterday handing me my favorite cup of coffee. or getting to take an hour walk this beautiful morning to pray & reflect, and taking another hour walk with my nieces & nephews. simple. beautiful. moments.  the moments that go unnoticed. but most of all - today i am giving thanks for the hard times. because the hard times are what we are usually never grateful for. it’s easy to be grateful for good things, but to actually be grateful for hard times? that’s where true faith comes in. so you want to know how to truly be thankful? give thanks for those hard things! 
james 1:2 says “dear brothers and sisters, when troubles come your way, consider it an opportunity for great joy.” true joy isn’t the opposite of trouble, it’s a choice you can have despite your trouble.
you can choose joy in the middle of a brokenness, painful memories, or even failing health.
through the power of the holy spirit, troubles might actually be your bridge to true thankfulness and happiness 💜

text:
yes that's us!! one of those crazy families that treats our pet as a hooman. but this cat isn't just any cat she is a huge part of family, and came into our life just at the right time, and i think we needed her just as much as she needed us. for 3 months she didn't want to go outside she was happy and content chilling with us inside. she has the most incredible instinct and is always there when we are sick, hurt or just not quite ourselves. there is so much love for this precious wee gem, and she has been a huge blessing for tara as well. despite the "presents" she has brought to me recently, i thought it was something cool to do with tara to show her that we should show love, kindness, and celebrate rusty for the special wee thing she is, yes she probably thinks we are mad, i don't care.
🌈🦄❤️🧡💛💚💙💜👩‍👧🎁🐈🎂🎉

text: happy thanksgiving/ happy thursday! holidays can be tough because the expectations of what they ‘should’ look like are so high and often unattainable. it doesn’t have to be your entire extended family, dressed up for a fancy home cooked dinner, pretending to like turkey. exercise your right to self care and let your people know that you are thankful for them. today i’m giving thanks for the health of my family, my education, and nature. enjoy your day, in whatever form it may take. #turkeyhottakes #mentalhealthmatters

text:
❌ #metoo ❌ •
do you know what i wish we didn't have to normalise?
talking about sexual abuse.
opening up about the trauma it causes, the deep roots it grows into abuse survivors and their generational lines, and the inseparable histories it shares with related mental health issues.
•
i've grappled for a long time about sharing my story. 
fear has held me back for so many reasons, some perhaps obvious and others i hadn't really anticipated but encountered whilst writing this post;
- what if no one believes me?
- who would care about something that happened over 10 years ago?
- how will people look at me now they know? will i seem like lesser of a person to them?
- what will my close friends and family who didn't know think?
•
trust me, i've probably thought about this more than anything in my life.
my past follows me everywhere;
- it is with me as i lie in bed at night,
- or when i walk down an empty alleyway,
- it is with me as i work,
- and it's sometimes with me as i am wrapped in a lovers embrace
•
so it's weird not to talk about this silent intruder that embedded itself in my family's tree, that became a part of me.
•
- 1 in 6 girls, and 1 in 9 boys below the age of 15 have experienced sexual assault
- 1 in 6 women, and 1 in 20 men since the age of 15 have experienced sexual assault
•
that is around an estimated 4.6 million people within australia (that have reported their abuse), or close to 20% of the population who have been affected by this taboo, detrimental and psychologically damaging event. •
this isn't an isolated issue, it doesn't limit itself to a particular demographic, socio-economic or age group. it can affect anyone. even that bright, bubbly girl who is smiling in the picture above 🙋‍♀️
•
i am an active supporter of the white ribbon organisation within australia, and stand for the oaths listed here: https://www.whiteribbon.org.au/stop-violence-against-women/supporter/ . become a supporter. open the conversation. stop the cycle. •
statistics: australian institute of health and welfare (2018), family, domestic and sexual violence in australia 2018, www.aihw.gov.au
•
support materials: 
https://au.reachout.com/ 
https://www.whiteribbon.org.au/

text:
égalité 👉🏽parce qu’il est detestable :
😡d’emprisonner des femmes du fait de leur volonté d’être libre en arabie saoudite (cf article du monde du 21/11/18) 👉🏽parce qu’il est intolérable :
😡d’exciser des petites filles dans le monde. 😡de forcer des femmes à se marier. ce phénomène concerne 700 millions de femmes au niveau international dont 250 millions de mineurs. 😡de pratiquer des avortements illégaux en inde enceinte d’une fille . 😡mais il est temps que les pays se donnent les moyens de changer leur regard sur les femmes dans les premiers cas, les familles peuvent obtenir le statut de réfugié politique (ceseda). 🌸association dans le 92 : #cada92. 👉🏽parce qu’il est insupportable :(30% des familles que j’accompagne) qu’une femme meurt tous les 3 jours sous les coups de son conjoint sans compter les conséquences souvent indélébiles sur les enfants. demandons plus de structures permettant les soins de ces hommes. 🌶il est aussi très  important de former les professionnels qui sont en contact avec ce public que ce soient les commissariats @justice_gouv pour pouvoir prendre la plainte de la personne (notamment les commissariats qui ne sont pratiquement pas formés), 🌶ou les autres professionnels du social afin s’il  sache écouter et l’orienter vers les associations dont j’ai déjà parlées dans ma parution du 6 juin. 
la journée internationale des violences faites aux femmes vous convie : -le samedi 24/11 à 14h (j’y serai) à la place de l’opera jusqu’à république (paris) . une femme a les mêmes droits qu’un homme, d’être indépendante financièrement, politiquement et intellectuellement etc .  @osez_le_feminisme . @cidff_paca @feminismm_ @fondationdesfemmes  @mouvementdunid #blancoynegro#noireetblancphotographie#blackandwhite#blackandwhitephotography#portraitphotography#femmes#feminisme#violenceagainstwomen#streetphotography#feminist#femme#1415mobilephotographers#silhouette#bnw_planet_2018#ig_bnw#bnw#reseaudes#lensculture#parisjetaime#igersfrance#streetphoto_bw#women#feminism#journeeviolencecontrelesfemmes#jesuisfeministe#noustoutes #metoo#💪🏾

text:
selbstbestimmung und freiheit. *anzeige (verlinkung)
das sind genau meine themen, denn ich habe immer wieder in meinem leben gemerkt, wie fremdbestimmt wir eigentlich sind. wie sehr v.a. wir frauen an andere gebunden sind. dies können die ehemänner sein, die familie im allgemeinen, aber auch der arbeitgeber. 
auch wenn ich mich schon sehr lange mit diesem thema befasse und meine meinen antrieb nach freiheit und selbstbestimmung zu kennen, gibt es immer wieder momente in denen sich in meinem gehirn eine verknüpfung auftut, die so noch nicht offensichtlich war. so auch jetzt. ob ich diesen text veröffentlichen werde weiß ich nicht, aber es tut gerade gut diese zeilen nieder zu schreiben. 
wer bei der #awesomepeopleconference von @robertgladitz in hamburg mit dabei war, weiß, dass es in meinem leben traumata gab, die u.a. zu ptbs, depressionen und massiven selbsthass geführt haben. ich habe die aus den traumata resultierenden folgen als ursache für meinen drang nach freiheit und selbstbestimmung gesehen, nicht aber die traumata selbst. dabei liegt genau hier der kern. die fremdbestimmung durch die depression - nicht mehr herrin über mein fühlen und handeln zu sein - ist das eine. aber die fremdbestimmung durch körperlichen und sexuellen missbrauch, jemandem ausgeliefert zu sein, sich nicht wehren können, alles immer und immer wieder über sich ergehen zu lassen ist etwas anderes. 
ein langer weg liegt hinter mir, ein weg der mich so stark gemacht hat, wie ich heute bin. ein weg ohne den ich heute nie an dem punkt wäre, an dem ich bin. ich bin dankbar, dass ich heute ich sein darf - frei und selbstbestimmt, meinen weg weiter gehen darf und so vielen frauen wie möglich helfen und begleiten darf auf ihrem weg zu mehr freiheit und selbstbestimmung. weil unser leben zu schön ist, um es zu verschwenden. .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
affischering idag med gula skyltar med texten "varning risk för sexuella trakasserier. vi har satt upp affischerna på stan för att visa på att risken för sexuella trakasserier finns överallt i samhället. både  i hemmet, på arbetsplatser och på offentliga platser. efter #metoo spreds kunskapen om att detta är ett samhällsproblem som inte bara drabbar enskilda personer utan är en del av ett större strukturellt problem. strukturella problem behöver lösas med strukturella lösningar och fi har politiken för det. vi står bakom de sju punkter som #metoo uppropen gemensam tog fram: 
använd metoo-uppropens expertis i statliga utredningar. 
satsa på sex-, samlevnads- och samtyckesundervisning. 
inför nationell visselblåsarfunktion för landets skolor. 
inför obligatoriska utbildningsmoment kring sexuellt våld. 
öka satsningen på stöd och behandling. 
skärp kraven på aktiva åtgärder och rapportering i arbetslivet. 
utred fler anmälningar om sexuella trakasserier i arbetslivet.
#fiskovde
name: Feministiskt Initiativ Skövde

text:
have you listened to/watched fr. #stendlrast on @ted ? today is a great day for it, but so is tomorrow or any other day. i had the pleasure of being close to him at @wisdom2conf a few years back, and he has an undeniable presence radiating from him, or practicing moment-to-moment #gratitude. sound like #mindfulness? yeah kind of, and a good entry point to #christians as he is a monk. 
two quotes to whet your appetite:
“what is the connection between happiness and gratefulness? many people would say, well, that's very easy. when you are happy, you are grateful. but think again. is it really the happy people that are grateful? we all know quite a number of people who have everything that it would take to be happy, and they are not happy, because they want something else or they want more of the same. and we all know people who have lots of misfortune, misfortune that we ourselves would not want to have, and they are deeply happy. they radiate happiness. you are surprised. why? because they are grateful. so it is not happiness that makes us grateful. it's gratefulness that makes us happy. if you think it's happiness that makes you grateful, think again. it's gratefulness that makes you happy.” “but once in a while, something very difficult is given to us, and when this difficult thing occurs to us, it's a challenge to rise to that opportunity, and we can rise to it by learning something which is sometimes painful. learning patience, for instance. we have been told that the road to peace is not a sprint, but is more like a marathon. that takes patience. that's difficult. it may be to stand up for your opinion, to stand up for your conviction. that's an opportunity that is given to us. to learn, to suffer, to stand up, all these opportunities are given to us, but they are opportunities, and those who avail themselves of those opportunities are the ones that we admire. they make something out of life. and those who fail get another opportunity. we always get another opportunity. that's the wonderful richness of life.” #happythanksgiving

text:
care about #metoo? in canada, a man is suing the woman who accused him of sexual assault and harassment and 20+ people who commented on the allegations. some defendants in the steven galloway suit are being sued for ‘defamation’ b/c they said ‘i believe her.’ this suit tries to create a dangerous precedent. push back by buying and wearing a #cantsilencesupport tee! it’s a fundraiser specifically for main complainant’s legal bills. m.c. will have some of the highest legal bills in the group (estimated at well into 6 figures!) and needs money urgently. the proceeds from these #cantsilencesupport shirts will go straight to her!
you can buy them on my website ahreaume.com. buying and wearing a #cantsilencesupport t-shirt is also a great way to send a message that lawsuits or the threat of lawsuits won’t silence the support of women who accuse powerful men of sexual assault and harassment. link in profile.

text:
on 23 november, @uni.lu is organising a forum for the elimination of #violenceagainstwomen, aiming at raising awareness of one of the most widespread, persistent and devastating human rights violations of our world today, which remains largely unreported due to the impunity, silence, stigma and shame surrounding it.

the forum will take place at the @luxembourg_learning_centre and will consist of two panels: 
roundtable 1: children and adolescents witnessing violence against women (moderated by violetta schaan)
1) pia mayer — one (office national de l’enfance) ministère de l’éducation nationale, de l’enfance et de la jeunesse
2) paul kremer — psychologist and psychotherapist alupse-dialogue
3) salima aarab — psychiatrie juvénile, hôpital kirchberg, hôpitaux robert schuman, luxembourg
4) laurence bouquet — chargée de direction, criminologue, phaemoberaterin riicht eraus - croix-rouge luxembourgeoise.
5) céline gerard — psychologue/psychothérapeute. responsable du psyea formatrice en matière de violence domestique.
6) leo pas (belgium) — medical doctor, past chair of the special interest group in family violence of the world organization of family doctors (wonca sigfv)

roundtable 2: violence against women (moderated by raquel gómez bravo)
1) andree birnbaum — directeure générale. femmes détresse.
2) danielle becker-bauer — présidente du zonta luxembourg
3) thorsten schwark — medical doctor, umedo, service médico-judiciaire, département médecine légale, laboratoire national de santé
4) sara rigon (italy) — medical doctor, msf
5) francis spautz — responsable du service infomann
6) valgerdur gunnarsdottir — european commission, dg health and food safety

the forum is organised under the auspices of the ministry of equal opportunities, le conseil national des femmes du luxembourg and zonta international. 👉 for more information and free registration please visit: http://orangeweek2018.eventbrite.com

#metoo #orangeweek #luxembourg #luxemburg #luxembourgville #belval #esch #uni_lu #letzebuerg #lussemburgo  #publichealth  @rqgb @youngzontaluxbg @zontaintl @wort_en @luxemburger_wort @lessentiel.lu #lessentiellu @lequotidienluxembourg @tageblatt.lu @letzjournal

text:
had the best thanksgiving brunch @barbacoa_boise !

i have been doing this bone broth cleanse that was amazing but was so excited to eat! 
this was one of the best buffets i have been to and i have been to literally a ton of them all over the world because i love buffets so much! i wish i had taken more pics of the various buffets i have been fortunate to eat at. 
there were so many options, traditional thanksgiving food, fresh seafood like oysters and shrimp, lobster ravioli, various empanada and flat breads, pulled pork, prime rib, soups, salads, and so many desserts! 
last night i was a bit lonely as can happen during the holidays when we are bombarded with advertising about how holidays should look and wished i had a family of my own and a big house with lots of cooking planned, etc.  in the past these feelings of inadequacy led me to escape with alcohol and ruin my holidays by poisoning my mind body and spirit. 
last night i did some foam rolling and took a bath and went to bed and my feelings of loneliness were replaced with gratitude for the freedom my life provides and the ability to enjoy such a wonderful experience today with my parents. i went to yoga and enjoyed the community and practice and know my happiness does not come from a hallmark holiday. 
sometimes these thoughts and lonely feelings are just randomly there, they leave just as fast as they come and we don't have to act on them. we can just pause, go to bed and wake up sober and thankful. 🙏
comparison is the theif of joy. the mind always wants to compare but it's not necessary, we can all enjoy a beautiful holiday season regardless of our relationship status 💛

text:
grateful for the lessons i learned in israel/ palestine: 
1-  compassionate activism: it is important to host different perspectives and not lose sight of the humanity of the people we vehemently disagree with. they all have a reason why they see the world the way they do. only from that can the most powerful form of and resistance emerge. our activism should come from a courageous heart full of love, not just our anger and fear.
2-  patience: “the arc of the moral universe is long, but it bends toward justice.” mlk. i know that the work i, and others, are engaged in is meaningful and necessary because it sets the ground for changes that are yet to come, even if i won’t get to see them. knowing it gives me hope and imbues my work with meaning.
3-  inevitability of pain: i used to be filled with so many “what ifs:” what if we never occupied those damn territories, what it the settlement project never existed, what if extremism never emerged. it’s pointless. and only serves to hang the blame on one side. history is a winding road i need to honor, even when it hurts. we don’t know the trajectory of events that ultimately swings back towards social change. for example, this american president is incredibly damaging on all fronts. and at the same time, he was an amplifier for social movements like #metoo (would it have erupted like that without him?) and powerful political awakening in this country. our pain is a catalyst for change. could change ever happen without it?
4-  no binaries: truth is plural. the only way to be right it to let go of being right. practice discernment, vulnerability, and question everything – especially your own beliefs. when you do that, you enter a conversational space with the universe that is truly miraculous, where possibilities for change are real. 
5-  please remember, between the trenches there are incredible people – teachers, healers, thinkers, mediators engaged in truly transformational work. we don’t hear about them. we don’t see them in the news. but there are there, resilient, creative, working against all odds. for all of them, i am truly grateful.

not many people could actually imagine you went through so many bad things in your young age and there will come other difficult times, ups and downs all along. but i’m going to tell you one thing,
you are a strong woman and one day you will have the strength to stand up and say enough is enough. i know it’s going to be hard and probably you will have times when you think i’ll just give up but believe me, it’s going to be worth it!
i choose my own way to do things even if people said it’s not going to happen, i did it anyway! i know i still have a long way to go and i’m far from the big goal but everyday is a next step closer to this goal, so be strong and believe in yourself 🥰

text: gabrielle union as julia rossmore in daddy's little girls (2007) | in this 200th post in the #herstaircasescene series gabrielle union celebrated. union has long been an outspoken feminist voice in hollywood, precursing many of the celebrity women that have started speaking out only fairly recently. among others, union has been a big supporter of planned parenthood for years now, as well as an active contributor to debates regarding mysogny, toxic masculinity, and rape culture. in her memoirs - we're going to need more wine - she also bravely shared the story of being raped herself. after the #metoo movement hit full steam, gabrielle also specfically asked to look beyond the high-profile stories of primarily white stars, to consider the experiences of all women. she is a hero of intersectional feminism.

#tbt 
2012 was a horrible year for several families in #colombia... women were being killed by their husbands, boyfriends, or just male friends. we marched for their lives, for justice, and the government had to listen to us somehow... today, i am commemorating a fight we, as family, gave for my sister, she would tell you her story about her shitty husband, but he thought he had the right to silent her life, he killed her in front of hundreds of people in a mall in #bogota and that’s why i am her voice in this planet. we fought for #justice 
that’s why i am an activist, that’s why i speak up, louder, and fight for the basic human rights for women. 
#bebold #fightlikeagirl #speakup #metoo #ellatambién #casoviviamurrego

text:
#medvilkenrätt #upptillbevis 🖤
för ett år sedan publicerades juristuppropet #medvilkenrätt som undertecknades av 5 964 kvinnor och icke-binära inom juristbranschen. följande krav ställdes: *vi kräver ett omedelbart slut på sexualiserande, marginaliserande, utnyttjande och nedvärderande av kvinnor i vår bransch. * vi kräver att de med maktpositioner i vår bransch – delägare på advokatbyråer, domstolschefer, chefer för myndigheter med flera – tar sitt ansvar. att de börjar agera med omsorg, slutar att blunda för övergrepp och ställer ansvariga till svars. * vi kräver att både kvinnor och män uppmuntras till att bryta tystnadskulturen på arbetsplatsen. den som vågar höja rösten ska inte straffas.

ett år senare förutsätts att ett gediget och evidensbaserat arbete förts för att säkerställa att ingen någonsin igen behöver vittna om missförhållanden på sin arbetsplats. det är nu hög tid för självrannsakan. är arbetsplatserna tryggare idag? hur har ni säkerställt att sexualiserande, marginaliserande, utnyttjande och nedvärderande av kvinnor i vår bransch upphört? att tystnadskulturen är bruten? hur skiljer sig dagens arbetsplats med den för ett år sedan? har ni arbetat förebyggande, uppmuntrat människor att höja rösten eller har ni straffat dem som vågar? 
vi som deltar i kampanjen #upptillbevis inom #medvilkenrätt gör det hand i hand, med en gemensam röst. vi vill se faktiska resultat: upp till bevis!
#metoo

text: did u notice i didn’t post a smiley pic for a while? infact i didn’t post v often for a while. it’s cause i was actually really unhappy. it’s good not to lie, even on social media. life fell apart right in front of me, & worse - inside of me. i lost sight of my vision, forgot my true mission, my goals faded on some old paper that i forgot to look at daily. i forgot saying empowering affirmations to myself, forgot to be grateful for... the life i had built for myself. so easily done. no one said 2018 would be easy. actually it was my hardest yet. ofc i wish i could change 100 things! but i wouldn’t change the person i have become because of the pain. grateful to be me, no matter the pain & the hard times, grateful to be the workaholic i am to get thru the darkest times. and into the light i say! welcome back smiler. it’s good to be home!!!!! 🌝 (wishing all of u share ur pain with someone... don’t suffer alone, & don’t hide away... it’s ok to feel everything & nothing, but it’s not ok to keep it to yourself).

text:
post vietato a chi non accetta che qualcuno abbia un parere diverso!

oggi è la giornata internazionale contro la violenza sulle donne e questo tema mi tocca in prima persona perché 
1 sono una donna 
2 in diversi momenti della mia vita ho assistito a violenze su donne,non donne qualsiasi ma amiche.
oggi voglio scriverle io due parole e non me ne frega niente se susciterò la vostra indignazione, se non mi vorrete più parlare, se mi cancellerete dagli amici(un che paura,anzi se lo fate mi fate un piacere).
ogni anno vengono spesi soldi per campagne pubblicitarie contro la violenza di genere,vengono spesi oceani di parole da chi soffre vedendo le proprie care venire maltrattate,ma purtroppo il problema principale è che,nonostante tutto, non si smetterà mai di assistere a situazioni del genere.
non si smetterà mai perché ci saranno donne che non lasceranno i loro fidanzati e i loro mariti.queste donne non si staccheranno mai da questi scogli.quello che continueranno a ripetere sarà la solita frase” cambierà “.
più che di lotta alla violenza si dovrebbe incrementare l’istruzione di queste ad essere indipendenti,di aumentare la loro autostima.la consapevolezza che noi possiamo anche senza un uomo e allo stesso tempo un uomo può fare anche senza una donna.il pulpito viene da una donna che ama un uomo ,un doppio senso di emozioni, due ,non uno.non un amore unilaterale,non un amore che scavalca ,ma due mondi che si incontrano e si allontanano quando è necessario un momento per esprimere se stessi.
allora sarà lì che potrà essere vinta questa battaglia.
spero un giorno di poter vivere in un mondo in cui ogni donna possa essere indipendente e decidere della sua vita quale sia la scelta giusta e quale quella sbagliata.
il mio discorso non è da femminista, ma non c’è dubbio che fino quando una donna,tornando a casa di notte ,dovrà guardarsi indietro per evitare che sia seguita, non ci sarà mai la sua indipendenza da qualsiasi altro genere!

text:
aut viam inveniam aut faciam - i will either find a way or make one. 
this time last year i was embarking on a  journey to have one of the best nights of my life. a night involving wrestling,  friends, subway, and giving lots of ... thanks. not knowing that night only set in motions series of a events that would dismantle my entire life. 
don't let love keep you in pain. don't let pain make you hard. find a way out. and if you can't find a way, make one. 
i'm so thankful i made my own way out. i'm so thankful for the people who have supported. who have believed. who have loved. who have cared. i would not have made it through this last year without you. 
#thanksgiving
#metoo
#fme

text:
hear me too ! 
our voices and stories must be heard. 
one in three women experience violence in their lifetime, across all social status, class, race, country or age group. that’s one too many. for many of them, the #metoo moment hasn’t come yet, because speaking out can have fatal consequences, and survival is a long and complicated journey.
join us on november 22 at the assembly hall lawns for our clothes line project as we recognize the international day for the elimination of violence against women 
#hearmetoo
#endingviolenceagainstwomen
#idevaw2018

text:
i’m not one to talk about my past because i don’t want it to define me. i don’t want to be defined by what i’ve survived and what i’ve endured. with that being said, it’s thanksgiving and i feel like should share on this one. the only way for me to express how thankful i am for these last few years it to open up about my past. i don’t like to celebrate holidays like this. every time i see a post on facebook about happy memories and happy childhoods i just feel sad. i feel sad because my childhood was filled with the lies and abuse of a man who let booze control his mind and his life and a woman who let him do what ever he wanted. the person in my life who was supposed to protect me and love me failed me in every possible way. on april 20, 2016 my mother and stepfather were arrested and everything changed. i am so thankful for everyone who was there that day. i’m thankful for the police and the detectives who worked my case and who believed when it felt like no one could believe such a horrible claim. i’m thankful for every cps worker, every social worker, every single person who has been with me these last two years. i’m thankful for everyone who has come in to my life, i can even express how thankful i am to all my friends for unknowingly showing me the world wasn’t completely horrible and could be full of such amazing and colorful people. for my family who stayed by my side and for holding my hand as my mother and stepfather were given 40 to life for their crimes. for holding me while i cried and laughing with me. i’m so thankful that i survived and that i’m still surviving. i’m thankful that i’m alive, and the the first time in many years, wanting to continue to live. i am so thankful for the last few years and i’m looking forward to everything that’s yet to come❤️ i am not a victim, i won’t let them take my name like that. i am a survivor and i am so unbelievably thankful for that.
.
.
.
.
#isurvived #imsurviving #imasurvivor #childabuseawareness #childabusesurvivor #childabuseprevention #awareness #abusesurvivor #rapeawareness #metoo #metoomovment  #rapesurvivor #metoomovement2018 #imfree #imsafe #imalive #thanksgiving #thankful #greatful

text:
ett år sen #metoo och #medvilkenrätt. nu är det #upptillbevis för arbetsgivarna att juristbranschen visst är att lita på. .

för ett år sedan publicerades juristuppropet #medvilkenrätt som undertecknades av 5 964 kvinnor och icke-binära inom juristbranschen. följande krav ställdes: *vi kräver ett omedelbart slut på sexualiserande, marginaliserande, utnyttjande och nedvärderande av kvinnor i vår bransch. . * vi kräver att de med maktpositioner i vår bransch – delägare på advokatbyråer, domstolschefer, chefer för myndigheter med flera – tar sitt ansvar. att de börjar agera med omsorg, slutar att blunda för övergrepp och ställer ansvariga till svars. . * vi kräver att både kvinnor och män uppmuntras till att bryta tystnadskulturen på arbetsplatsen. den som vågar höja rösten ska inte straffas. .

ett år senare förutsätts att ett gediget och evidensbaserat arbete förts för att säkerställa att ingen någonsin igen behöver vittna om missförhållanden på sin arbetsplats. det är nu hög tid för självrannsakan. är arbetsplatserna tryggare idag? hur har ni säkerställt att sexualiserande, marginaliserande, utnyttjande och nedvärderande av kvinnor i vår bransch upphört? att tystnadskulturen är bruten? hur skiljer sig dagens arbetsplats med den för ett år sedan? har ni arbetat förebyggande, uppmuntrat människor att höja rösten eller har ni straffat dem som vågar? .

vi som deltar i kampanjen #upptillbevis inom #medvilkenrätt gör det hand i hand, med en gemensam röst. vi vill se faktiska resultat: upp till bevis!

text: #thursdaythoughts ... and hey la—i need a favor! some of you may have heard that i'm working on a new documentary series exploring issues around identity— from women, sex and power to, more broadly, people of various backgrounds and perspectives, navigating our increasingly complex relationships to each other and our world. for example, as a cis-gender woman living in our current #metoo, #timesup reality, i’m trying to answer questions for myself, like what kind of progress are we making? what’s changed in the workplace? in our home lives? in dating? and how have men’s experiences changed, if at all? which is why for my first foray into this project, i, and a few of my ‘friends’, are planning to talk to men -- woke or otherwise -- and ask what they think about all this.  so, if you're a man in the los angeles area (all ages/backgrounds are welcome) and are interested in sharing your thoughts on-camera, please get in touch with my producer erin at e.crumpacker@imagine-entertainment.com - we'll be filming early december and would love to include your voice!  also, women and people of all genders: feel free to nominate your bf or brother or father (who may or may not be on social media)...and even that uncle you only see at thanksgiving, the one who wears his #maga hat to the table—yep, i want to talk to him, too. thanks! and speaking of, whatever ‘thanksgiving’ means to you, i’m sending you love and gratitude. 💕
